label: rooftop photovoltaic power plant
definition: A rooftop photovoltaic power plant is a photovoltaic power plant that is installed on top of the roof of a building.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): agriculture, forestry and fishing
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'agriculture, forestry and fishing' is an energy demand sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions from fuel combustion in agriculture, forestry, fishing and fishing industries such as fish farms.

label: plug-in hybrid electric vehicle
definition: A plug-in hybrid electric vehicle (PHEV) is a vehicle that contains both an electric traction motor and an internal combustion engine and can switch between their usage for propulsion. It contains a traction battery that can be charged with electrical energy from an external supply.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): incineration and open burning of waste
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'incineration and open burning of waste' is a waste and wastewater sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Incineration of waste and open burning waste, not including waste-to-energy facilities.

label: factsheet
definition: A factsheet is a document that collects information about a specific topic in a structured way.

label: waste power plant
definition: A waste power plant is a power plant that has waste power units as parts.

label: biodiesel
definition: Biodiesel is a portion of matter that has a liquid state of matter and has a diesel fuel role. It is produced from plants or animals and thus has a biogenic origin.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): electrical equipment
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'electrical equipment' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Electrical equipment is used in the transmission and distribution of electricity above 1 kV. SF6 is used in gasinsulated switchgear (GIS), gas circuit breakers (GCB), gas-insulated transformers (GIT), gas-insulated lines (GIL), outdoor gas-insulated instrument transformers, reclosers, switches, ring main units and other equipment.

label: ampere
definition: "An electric current unit which is equal to the constant current which, if maintained in two straight parallel conductors of infinite length, of negligible circular cross-section, and placed 1 m apart in vacuum, would produce between these conductors a force equal to 2 x 10^[-7] newton per meter of length." [BIPM:BIPM, NIST:NIST]

label: apinist
definition: An apinist is an OEP user who mainly interacts via an API.

label: square millimeter
definition: "An area unit which is equal to one millionth of a square meter or 10^[-6] m^[2]." [NIST:NIST]

label: energy use
definition: Energy use is the consumption of an energy carrier making use of the energy it carries.

label: square kilometer
definition: An area unit which is equal to one million square meters or 10^[6] m^[2].

label: commissioning start
definition: A commissioning start is a start time that indicates the beginning of a commissioning time.

label: million ton of coal equivalent
definition: A million ton of coal equivalent is an energy unit which is equal to 1,000,000 tons of coal equivalent.

label: scenario study
definition: A scenario study is a study that investigates one or more scenarios.

label: biofuel power unit
definition: A biofuel power unit is a power generating unit using biofuel.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): public electricity and heat production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'public electricity and heat production' is an energy transformation sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Sum of emissions from main activity producers of electricity generation, combined heat and power generation, and heat plants.

label: fuel demand
definition: Fuel demand is the energy demand for fuel.

label: C++
definition: C++ is a programming languages designed by Bjarne Stroustrup and standardised by ISO/IEC.

label: simulation
definition: A simulation is a model calculation that simulates a process or system behaviour from the real world.

label: non-methane volatile organic compound
definition: A non-methane volatile organic compound (NMVOC) is a volatile organic compound other than methane.

label: steam reformer
definition: A steam reformer is an energy converting component that produces syngas from hydrocarbons such as natural gas.

label: waterway network
definition: A waterway network is a transport network that enables transport on water.

label: sensible fluid heat storage object
definition: A sensible fluid heat storage object is a sensible heat storage that uses fluids (like water, oil, …) to store thermal energy.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): industrial processes and product use - other
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'industrial processes and product use - other' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories

label: car
definition: A car is a motorised road vehicle that is used for passenger transport and has a maximum of eight seats.

label: policy
definition: A policy is a plan specification that is a deliberate system of principles, rules and guidelines, adopted by an organisation to guide decision making with respect to particular situations and implemented to achieve stated goals.

label: journal article
definition: A report that is published in a journal.

label: technology
definition: A technology is a plan specification that describes how to combine artificial objects or other material entities and processes in a specific way.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): industrial processes and product use
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'energy industrial processes and product use' (IPPU) is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
It covers greenhouse gas emissions occurring from industrial processes, from the use of greenhouse gases in products, and from non-energy uses of fossil fuel carbon.

label: HVDC-line
definition: An HVDC-line is a powerline for transferring high voltage direct current.

label: data processing
definition: data processing is a transformation in which a data item gets transformed.

label: energy balance collection
definition: An energy balance collection is a data set of energy balances for various time steps and/or temporal regions.

label: provider
definition: A provider is an agent that transfers commodities or services to other agents.

label: renewable energy
definition: A renewable energy is an energy that has renewable origin.

label: spatial planning policy
definition: Spatial planning policy is a policy of a German federal state that designates portions of a spatial region to purposes like settlement, infrastructur and sustainability.

label: scenario bundle
definition: A scenario bundle is an information content entity that connects information about a scenario study and the associated scenario projections on the OEP via the OEKG.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): fuel combustion - other
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'fuel combustion' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
All remaining emissions from fuel combustion that are not specified elsewhere. Include emissions from fuel delivered to the military in the country and delivered to the military of other countries that are not engaged in multilateral operations.

label: energy storage function
definition: An energy storage function is the function of an artificial object that has been engineered to contain energy for later usage whereby input energy and usable output energy are of the same type.

label: volatility
definition: The volatility disposition is the disposition of a portion of matter to sublimate or evaporate from the solid or liquid form and enter the surrounding air.

label: gasoline car
definition: A gasoline car is a car that has only a gasoline engine as motor for propulsion and thus is also a gasoline vehicle.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): integrated circuit or semiconductor
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'integrated circuit or semiconductor' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions of CF4, C2F6, C3F8, c-C4F8, C4F6, C4F8O, C5F8, CHF3, CH2F2, NF3 and SF6 from uses of these gases in Integrated Circuit (IC) manufacturing in rapidly evolving ways and in varying amounts, which depend on product
(e.g., memory or logic devices) and equipment manufacturer.

label: scenario
definition: A scenario is an information content entity that contains statements about a possible future development based on a coherent and internally consistent set of assumptions and their motivation.

label: sewage plant
definition: A sewage plant is an artificial object that removes contaminants from wastewater to produce an effluent that is suitable for discharge to the surrounding environment or an intended reuse application.

label: hecto
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of one hundred." [UO:GVG]

label: EU emission sector: ETS
definition: The EU emission sector ETS is a sector defined by an EU emission sector division that covers greenhouse gas emissions that are regulated by the European Union Emissions Trading System.

label: nature of model uncertainty
definition: Nature of model uncertainty is a quality of a model that represents the core reason for uncertainty within it.

label: weekly
definition: one value per week

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): cropland
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'cropland' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions and removals from arable and tillage land, rice fields, and agro-forestry systems where vegetation falls below the thresholds used for the forest land category.

label: waste thermal energy
definition: Waste thermal energy is thermal energy that is the physical output of an energy transformation process and that is released into the environment unused.

label: economic instrument function
definition: An economic instrument function is a function of a policy instrument that promotes, amongst others, economic measures.

label: fuel
definition: A fuel is a portion of matter that has the disposition to be an energy carrier and that has a fuel role.

label: watt per square meter
definition: "An irradiance unit which is equal to 1 watt of radiant power incident per one square meter surface area." [NIST:NIST]

label: combined heat and power generating unit
definition: A combined heat and power generating unit is an energy transformation unit that has both the function to produce thermal energy and the function to produce electrical energy.

label: fuel tank
definition: A fuel tank is a tank that stores a combustion fuel.

label: megaHertz
definition: "A frequency unit which is equal to one million hertz or 10^[6] V." [UOC:GVG]

label: petawatt-hour
definition: A petawatt-hour is a watt-hour based unit which is equal to 10^15 watt-hours.

label: pumped hydro storage power technology
definition: A pumped hydro storage power technology is a power generation technology that describes how to combine hydro power units in pumped hydro storage power plants and a hydroelectric energy transformation.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): N2O from product use
gas turbine compressor station

label: megawatt
definition: A power unit which is equal to one million watts.

label: heat plant
definition: A heat plant is an energy transformation unit consisting of heat generating units and a grid component that feeds thermal energy into a heating grid.

label: flow potential
definition: A flow potential is a potential of an input or output of a process, per time unit.

label: non-metallic mineral
definition: A non-metallic mineral is a mineral that does not contain any metallic content within themselves. It is the physical output of an industrial process and has a commodity role.

label: emission price
definition: An emission price is a monetary price of emitting a certain emission value.

label: year
definition: "A time unit which is equal to 12 months which in science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: grid component
definition: A grid component is an energy transformation unit that is a discrete part of a supply grid serving a specific purpose.

label: kilogram
definition: "A mass unit which is equal to the mass of the International Prototype Kilogram kept by the BIPM at Svres, France." [BIPM:BIPM, NIST:NIST]

label: electricity import value
definition: An electricity import value is an electrical energy amount value that measures the import of electrical energy.

label: CO2 price
definition: A CO2 price is an emission price of emitting a certain CO2 emission value.

label: Brent crude
definition: Brent crude is a crude oil that is extracted in the North Sea and traded at ICE London.

label: energy scenario
definition: An energy scenario is a scenario that describes a possible future state of an energy system.

label: gas turbine
definition: A gas turbine is a turbine that participates in a gas turbine process. It is also called combustion turbine.

label: renewable energy share
definition: A renewable energy share is a process attribute that indicates the fraction of renewable energy related to the total energy of an energy generation or consumption process.

label: secondary control
definition: A secondary control is a frequency control that is centralised and automated. It refers to the control area of one transmission system operator. Secondary control succeeds primary control and operates for several minutes.

label: process profile
definition: b is a process_profile =Def. there is some process c such that b process_profile_of c (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [093-002])

label: ambient thermal energy transfer
definition: Ambient thermal energy transfer is a heat transfer from the ambient air to a transportable material entity.

label: metal
definition: A metal is a portion of matter consisting of an atom of an element that exhibits typical metallic properties, being typically shiny, with high electrical and thermal conductivity.

label: bridge
definition: A bridge is a transport network component that spans a physical obstacle without blocking the way underneath.

label: manufactured coal based gas
definition: A manufactured coal based gas is a gas mixture that is manufactured from coal. It is used as fossil fuel.

label: apply constraints for assessment of potential
definition: Apply constraints for assessment of potential is an action specification that describes the process of integrating non-technical factors, such as social acceptance, land use regulations, or market conditions, into the potential assessment.

label: lignite power plant
definition: A lignite power plant is a coal power plant that has lignite power units as parts.

label: transport
definition: Transport is the process of moving people or goods from one place to another.

label: biogas
definition: Biogas is a gas mixture produced by anaerobic digestion. It consists mainly of methane and carbon dioxide and can be used as fuel.

label: vehicle operational mode
definition: A vehicle operational mode is a realizable entity that determines how a vehicle is operating.

label: fuel commodity role
definition: Fuel commodity role is the commodity role of fuels.

label: steam
definition: Steam is water that has a gaseous state of matter.

label: pump
definition: A pump is an energy converting component that converts energy into kinetic or potential energy of a fluid.

label: energy storage content
definition: An energy storage content is an energy amount value that measures the quantity of energy stored in an energy storage object.

label: boolean value
definition: A boolean value is an variable information content entity that can only be true or false.

label: radiation
definition: Radiation is an energy transfer by emitting or transmitting energy in the form of waves or particles through a spatial region or a material entity.

label: information content entity
definition: A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

label: data item
definition: A data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): non-energy products from fuels and solvent use
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'non-energy products from fuels and solvent use' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
The use of oil products and coal-derived oils primarily intended for purposes other than combustion

label: urban population
definition: An urban population is a population living in urban areas, as defined by national statistical offices.

label: cubic centimeter
definition: "A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a cubic meter or 10^[-9] m^[3], or to 1 ml." [NIST:NIST]

label: electricity grid
definition: An electricity grid is a supply grid that distributes electrical energy / electricity.

label: delimiter separated file format
definition: A delimiter separated file format is a text file format that uses delimiter-separated values (also DSV) to store two-dimensional arrays of data by separating the values in each row with specific delimiter characters.

label: electrochemical reaction
definition: An electrochemical reaction is a chemical reaction that describes the overall reactions of individual redox reactions being separated but connected by an external electric circuit and an intervening electrolyte.

label: diesel truck
definition: A diesel truck is a truck that has only a diesel engine as motor for propulsion and thus is also a diesel vehicle.

label: gasoline engine
definition: A gasoline engine is an internal combustion engine that uses a gasoline fuel.

label: resilience
definition: Resilience is a disposition of a system that represents the capacity of a system to absorb disturbance and reorganize so as to retain essentially the same function, structure, and feedbacks.

label: nuclear electric hydrogen
definition: Nuclear electrolytic hydrogen is electrolytic hydrogen that is produced with nuclear electrical energy.

label: potential
definition: A potential is a maximum value that describes some upper limit in a spatial region of reference.

label: flat-plate collector
definition: A flat-plate collector is a solar thermal collector that consists of flat-plates.

label: zetta
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 21." [UO:GVG]

label: liquid air production
definition: Liquid air production is a production that produces liquid air by cooling and compressing (gaseous) air.

label: heat generating unit
definition: A heat generating unit is an energy transformation unit that has the function to produce thermal energy.

label: marine wave energy
definition: Marine wave energy is the natural hydro energy of a wave.

label: regionalisation
definition: Regionalisation is a methodology to calculate spatially distributed energy producers and consumers with the aim to highlight regional differences in energy supply and potentials, particularly related to renewable energies.

label: fuel cell electric vehicle
definition: A fuel cell electric vehicle (FCEV) is an electric vehicle that uses electrical energy from a fuel cell.

label: solar electrolytic hydrogen
definition: Solar electrolytic hydrogen is electrolytic hydrogen that is produced with solar electrical energy.

label: energy conversion efficiency
definition: Energy conversion efficiency is a process attribute describing the ratio between the input of an energy transformation and the outputs that are used.

label: electric compressor station
definition: An electric compressor station is a compressor station that has en elecrtric motor for driving the compressor.

label: freight train
definition: A freight train is a train that is used for freight transport.

label: volatile organic compound
definition: A volatile organic compound (VOC) is a portion of matter consisting of organic compounds that is capable of producing photochemical oxidants by reactions with nitrogen oxides in the presence of sunlight. Hence it can act as an air pollutant.

label: model calculation
definition: A model calculation is a process of solving mathematical equations of a model.

label: scenario projection comparison
definition: A scenario comparison study is a scenario study that performs a scenario projection comparison

label: E10
definition: E10 is a gasoline fuel that consists of (fossil) gasoline and up to 10 % ethanol and that is liquid.

label: primary energy carrier mining
definition: Primary energy carrier mining is a primary energy production that recovers non-renewable energy carriers from its natural site.

label: political assumption
definition: A political assumption is an assumption about political measures taken.

label: copyright licence
definition: A copyright licence is a licence that states the ownership and contractually sets the rights and obligations to use, copy, and distribute a creative work.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): agriculture - other
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'agriculture - other' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories

label: energy converting component
definition: An energy converting component is an artificial object that is usually a discrete part of an energy transformation unit with the function of transforming, transferring or changing a certain type of energy.

label: water turbine
definition: A water turbine is a turbine converting potential energy and kinetic energy of water into rotational energy.

label: power-to-liquid process
definition: A power-to-liquid process is a power-to-fuel process that converts electrical energy to chemical energy by synthesising portions of matter into a liquid synthetic fuel.

label: equipment cost
definition: Equipment cost is an investment cost for acquisition of the components and machinery including environmental facilities.

label: internal combustion engine
definition: An internal combustion engine is a motor that converts chemical energy into kinetic energy using a cyclic combustion process.

label: capacity premium
definition: A capacity premium is a market premium that guarantees remuneration for reserving capacity of energy transformation units to be available for unexpected events.

label: source category
definition: A source category is a sector that is defined by a common reporting format.

label: system robustness
definition: System robustness is a disposition of a system that is designed or evolved in such a way as to be resistant to total failure despite partial damage or external changes.

label: photovoltaic cell
definition: A photovoltaic cell (PV cell) is a generator that converts solar energy into electrical energy.

label: energy carrier disposition
definition: An energy carrier disposition is a disposition of an material entity that contains energy for conversion as usable energy.

label: power generating unit
definition: A power generating unit is an energy transformation unit that has the function to produce electrical energy.

label: common reporting format
definition: The common reporting format (CRF) is a sector division used for compiling national inventory reports on greenhouse gas emissions and providing emission relevant data in so called CRF tables.

label: surface
definition: A surface is a tangential proper part of an object that extends in two dimensions.

label: KSG sector transport
definition:
The KSG sector transport is a transport sector defined by the KSG sector division. It is an aggregate of the following four sectors:
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): domestic aviation (CRF 1.A.3.a)
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): road transportation (CRF 1.A.3.b)
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): railways (CRF 1.A.3.c)
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): domestic navigation (CRF 1.A.3.d)

label: length unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: natural ambient thermal energy
definition: Natural ambient thermal energy is ambient thermal energy that has a renewable origin.

label: priority region with effect of suitable region
definition: A priority region with effect of suitable region is a region of relevance that has both the priority region role and the suitable region role.

label: nuclear electrical energy
definition: Nuclear electrical energy is electrical energy with a nuclear origin.

label: watt
definition: "A power unit which is equal to the power used when work is done at the rate of 1 joule per second." [NIST:NIST]

label: nace_ sectors
definition:
The Statistical classification of economic activities in the European Community, abbreviated as NACE, is the classification of economic activities in the European Union (EU); the term NACE is derived from the French Nomenclature statistique des activités économiques dans la Communauté européenne. Various NACE versions have been developed since 1970.

NACE is a four-digit classification providing the framework for collecting and presenting a large range of statistical data according to economic activity in the fields of economic statistics (e.g. production, employment and national accounts) and in other statistical domains developed within the European statistical system (ESS).

label: institution
definition: An institution is an organisation that serves a social purpose.

label: full load hours
definition: Full load hours are a quantity value that describes the utilization of a technical device. The value of the full load hours is obtained by dividing the annual amount of energy generated by the declared net capacity of the plant.

label: water flow rate
definition: Water flow rate is the process attribute of water flow that quantifies the water volume per time unit.

label: solar chemical energy transformation
definition: A solar chemical energy transformation is a solar energy transformation that converts solar energy into chemical energy.

label: PM2.5
definition: PM2.5 is particulate matter which passes through a size-selective inlet as defined in the reference method for the sampling and measurement of PM2,5, EN 14907, with a 50 % efficiency cut-off at 2,5 µm aerodynamic diameter.

label: giga
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 9." [UO:GVG]

label: transport performance value
definition: A transport performance value is a quantity value that indicates the performance of a transport process in terms of its mileage and amount of transported people and/or goods.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): settlements
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'settlements' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions and removals from all developed land, including transportation infrastructure and human settlements of any size, unless they are already included under other categories.

label: volumetric flow rate value
definition: A volumetric flow rate value is a quantity value that has a volumetric flow rate unit as unit.

label: marine wave energy technology
definition: A marine wave energy technology is a marine hydro power technology that describes how to combine marine wave energy converting units in marine wave energy transformations.

label: Effort Sharing Regulation
definition: The Effort Sharing Regulation (ESR) is the European effort sharing for the years 2021-2030. It covers the European Union, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein and the following greenhouse gases: carbon dioxide, methane, nitrous oxide, hydrofluorocarbons, perfluorocarbons, sulphur hexafluoride and nitrogen trifluoride. Emission quantities under the ESR are calculated using global warming potentials from the Fifth IPCC Assessment Report.

label: coal
definition: Coal is a portion of matter consisting of combustible black or brownish-black sedimentary rock, formed as rock strata called coal seams.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): soda ash production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'soda ash production' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Soda ash (sodium carbonate, Na2CO3) is a white crystalline solid that is used as a raw material in a large number of industries including glass manufacture, soap and detergents, pulp and paper production and water treatment. Emissions of CO2 from the production of soda ash vary dependent on the manufacturing process. Four different processes may be used to produce soda ash. Three of these processes, monohydrate, sodium sesquicarbonate (trona) and direct carbonation, are referred to as natural processes. The fourth, the Solvay process, is classified as a synthetic process.

label: currency
definition: A unit which is a measure of the medium of an exchange value, defined by reference to the geographical location of the monetary authorities responsible for it.

label: report
definition: A document assembled by an author for the purpose of providing information for the audience. A report is the output of a documenting process and has the objective to be consumed by a specific audience. Topic of the report is on something that has completed. A report is not a single figure. Examples of reports are journal article, patent application, grant progress report, case report (not patient record).

label: carbon dioxide equivalent quantity value
definition: A carbon dioxide equivalent quantity is a greenhouse gas emission value that quantifies the combined effect of all emitted greenhouse gases by giving an equivalent amount of CO2 which would have the same effect on the climate.

label: explorative scenario
definition: An explorative scenario is a scenario that contains certain constraints / statements regarding measures that are taken in the near future / today to explore where these measures will lead to in a later future. The later future is not predefined in the scenario.

label: wind farm area determination process

label: gasoline fuel

label: non associated gas

label: pH
definition: "A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the acidity of a solution in terms of activity of hydrogen ions (H+)." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: run of river power plant

label: ammonia

label: data center

label: interacting region role

label: written name

label: oil power unit

definition: A biofuel power plant is a power plant that has biofuel power units as parts.

label: synthetic ammonia

label: geothermal energy

label: power-to-ammonia process
definition: A power-to-ammonia process is a power-to-gas process that has ammonia as output.

label: coke oven gas

label: renewable energy share value

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): electronics industry - other

label: export

label: geothermal heat unit
definition: A geothermal heat unit is a heat transfer unit that uses geothermal energy as source.

label: gas turbine process

label: two axis tracked receiving surface

label: solar tracked receiving surface
definition: A solar tracked receiving surface is a solar radiation receiving surface that participates in solar tracking.

label: tangential proper part

label: waste and wastewater sector
definition: A waste and wastewater sector is a sector that covers activities related the collection and treatment of waste and wastewater.

definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) international bunkers is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories. It encompasses international bunkers and multilateral operation.

label: manufactured material
definition: A manufactured material is a portion of matter that is the physical output of a manufacturing process and that has a good role.

label: grid component link

label: coal power unit

label: KSG sector division
definition: The KSG sector division is a CRF-based sector division defined in annex 1 of the Bundes-Klimaschutzgesetz (KSG).

label: gaseous fossil fuel
