definition: An energy demand sector is a sector that covers energy consumers.

label: sustainability criterion
definition: A sustainability criterion is a plan specification that intends to meet the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own environmental, economic and social needs.

label: battery electric car
definition: A battery electric car is a car that has an electric traction motor and a traction battery and thus is also a battery electric vehicle.

label: obsolete economic value
definition: OBSOLETE: An economic value is a quantity value that is economically relevant.

label: gross domestic product
definition: A gross domestic product is a quantity value that represents the broadest measure of aggregate economic activity, measuring the total unduplicated market value of all final goods and services produced within a statistical area in a period.

label: minute
definition: "A time unit which is equal to 60 seconds." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: KSG sector waste management and other
definition:
The KSG sector waste management and other is a sector defined by the KSG sector division. It is an aggregate of the following two sectors:
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): waste (CRF 5)
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): other (CRF 6)

label: labour force
definition: The labour force is the population of people ages 15 and older who supply labour to the production of goods and services.  It includes people who are currently employed and people who are unemployed but seeking work as well as first-time job-seekers.

label: EU allowance
definition: An EU Allowance (EUA) is an emission certificate used in the European Union Emissions Trading System (EU ETS). It permits the emission of a CO2 equivalent quantity of 1 tonne.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): oil and natural gas
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'oil and natural gas' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Comprises fugitive emissions from all oil and natural gas activities.

label: aviation gasoline
definition: Aviation gasoline is gasoline used as motor spirit and prepared especially for aviation piston engines, with an octane number suited to the engine, a freezing point of -60 °C and a distillation range usually within the limits of 30 °C and 180 °C.

label: conduction unit
definition: "A unit which represents a standard measurement of the transmission of an entity through a medium." [UOC:GVG]

label: hard coal power technology
definition: A hard coal power technology is a coal power technology that describes how to combine hard coal power units and hard coal in a fuel-powered electricity generation process.

label: carbon tax
definition: Carbon tax is a tax for emitting CO2 or other greenhouse gases (measured in CO2 equivalent values).

label: delivery time point
definition: A delivery time point is a zero-dimensional temporal region expressing the point in time when goods that have been bought arrive at the place where they are wanted.

label: scenario time series
definition: A scenario time series is a time series that contains data about a specific scenario year.

label: NC/BR sector: agriculture
definition: The NC/BR sector "agriculture" is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by an NC/BR sector division. It aligns to the CRF sector (IPCC 2006): agriculture.

label: priority region role
definition: A priority region role is a role of a region of interest that gives high priority to building wind park projects, excluding building projects that are not compatible with this priority.

label: combustion
definition: Combustion is an exothermic redox reaction between a fuel (the reductant) and an oxidant (usually atmospheric oxygen) which is initiated by a ignition source.

label: non-energy use technology
definition: A non-energy use technology is a technology that describes among other things how to combine the consumption of energy carriers for non-energy use with other processes and artificial objects or other material entities in a specific way.

label: level of model uncertainty
definition: Level of model uncertainty is a quality of a model that represents the degree or severity of an uncertainty.

label: Effort Sharing Decision
definition: The Effort Sharing Decision (ESD) is the European effort sharing for the years 2013-2020. It covers the European Union, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein and the following greenhouse gases: carbon dioxide, methane, nitrous oxide, hydrofluorocarbons, perfluorocarbons and sulphur hexafluoride. Emission quantities under the ESD are calculated using global warming potentials from the Fourth IPCC Assessment Report.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): other process uses of carbonates
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'other process uses of carbonates' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Includes limestone, dolomite and other carbonates etc. Emissions from the use of limestone, dolomite and other carbonates should be included in the industrial source category where they are emitted. Therefore, for example, where a carbonate is used as a flux for iron and steel production, resultant emissions should be reported under 2C1 “Iron and Steel Production” rather than this
subcategory.

label: geogenic
definition: Geogenic is an origin of portions of matter or energies that are the result of geological processes.

label: particulate matter
definition: Particulate matter is a portion of matter consisting of small particles. It can act as an air pollutant.

label: non-sustainable biofuel
definition: A non-sustainable biofuel is a biofuel that does not conform to sustainability criteria.

label: combustion fuel
definition: A combustion fuel is a fuel that realises its fuel role in processes that release energy in the form of heat or work by chemical reaction with other substances.

label: fluid
definition: A fluid is a material entity which is a liquid, gas or plasma.

label: property cost
definition: A property cost is an investment cost arising from the acquisition of a property.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): fuel combustion - other sectors
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'fuel combustion - other sectors' is an energy demand sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions from combustion activities as described below, including combustion for the generation of electricity and heat for own use in these sectors.

label: bidirectional vehicle charging station
definition: A bidirectional vehicle charging station is a vehicle charging station that can also feed electrical energy from the traction battery back into the electricity grid.

label: gas engine
definition: A gas engine is an internal combustion engine that uses a gaseous combustion fuel.

label: price request
definition: A price request is a request in which an agent asks another agent for a price.

label: substitution method
definition: A substitution method is a primary energy consumption calculation method that treats renewable energy carriers as if they have similar conversion losses as a specified fossil reference energy carrier.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): land use, land-use change and forestry
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'land use, land-use change and forestry' (LULUCF) is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories

label: plan specification
definition: A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts, and that may be concretized as a realizable entity that, if realized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

label: user documentation
definition: A user documentation is a documentation intended to assist users in using the software.

label: passenger transport
definition: A passenger transport is a transport process in which people are moved in a vehicle from one place to another.

label: e-bike
definition: An e-bike is a bicycle that is propelled by a person and an electric traction motor.

label: potential energy
definition: Potential energy is the energy that a material entity contains due to its position relative to other material entities or to stresses within itself.

label: flow battery
definition: A flow battery is a battery in which chemical energy is provided by two chemical components dissolved in liquids contained within the system and separated by a membrane. Ion exchange (accompanied by flow of electric current) occurs through the membrane while both liquids circulate in their own respective space.

label: primary energy consumption calculation method
definition: A primary energy consumption calculation method is a methodology to calculate primary energy consumption.

label: increase
definition: A process of becoming larger, more numerous, more important, or more likely.

label: radian
definition: "A plane angle unit which is equal to the angle subtended at the center of a circle by an arc equal in length to the radius of the circle, approximately 57 degrees 17 minutes and 44.6 seconds." [NIST:NIST]

label: marine thermal energy transfer
definition: Marine thermal energy transfer is a heat transfer from the marine water body to a transportable material entity.

label: wind characteristics determination process
definition:
Wind characteristics determination process is a process that follows a determination methodology for wind characteristics to gain knowledge of the specific wind characteristics of a predefined region.
Wind characteristics include speed, direction, frequency, turbulence, and seasonal or diurnal patterns.

label: unit
definition: A unit of measurement is a generically dependent continuant that represents a standardised quantity value of a quantifiable entity

label: quality control flag
definition: A quality control flag is a data descriptor that describes the measurement quality of a data set, e.g. a time series.

label: non-ferrous metal
definition: A non-ferrous metal is a metal that does not contain a significant amount of iron in its chemical composition. It is the physical output of an industrial process and has a commodity role.

label: decommissioning end
definition: A decommissioning end is an end time that indicates the beginning of a decommissioning time.

label: direct marketer
definition: A direct marketer is a trader who is the relay between the energy exchange and power plant operators.

label: calculate levelised cost of electricity
definition: Calculate levelised cost of electricity is an action specification that describes the computation of the levelised cost of electricity (LCOE) either for individual turbines or for sub-regions within the study area by applying a cost model based on the previously calculated economic parameters and the capacity factors.

label: carbon capture
definition: Carbon capture is a process that captures carbon dioxide from a gas.

label: monetary value
definition: A monetary value is a quantity value that states the amount of money specified in monetary units.

label: airport
definition: An airport is a transport hub for airplanes.

label: notation key
definition: A notation key is a missing value reason defined by the UNFCCC to indicate why data is missing.

label: software library
definition: A software library is software composed of a collection of software modules and/or software methods in a form that can be statically or dynamically linked to some software application.

label: oxidation
definition: Oxidation is a chemical reaction that describes the loss of electrons of an atom, an ion, or of certain atoms in a molecule and is a part of a redox reaction.

label: gas vehicle
definition: A gas vehicle is an internal combustion vehicle that has only a gas engine as a motor for propulsion.

label: marine current energy transformation
definition: Marine current energy transformation is a hydroelectric energy transformation that converts marine current energy to electrical energy.

label: investment cost
definition: Investment costs are costs of a long-term commitment of financial resources in tangible or intangible assets.

label: degree Celsius
definition: "A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K." [NIST:NIST]

label: syngas
definition: Syngas is a gas mixture consisting primarily of hydrogen, carbon monoxide, and very often carbon dioxide, that can be used as fuel.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): fugitive emissions from fuels
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'fugitive emissions from fuels' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Includes all intentional and unintentional emissions from the extraction, processing, storage and transport of solid fuel to the point of final use.

label: solid
definition: The state being solid. A portion of matter is in solid state if and only if it has a definite shape and volume (at a given temperature and pressure).

label: theoretical flow potential
definition: A theoretical flow potential is a type of flow potential that identifies the physical upper limit of an input or output of a process in a spatial region of reference per unit time.

label: electricity transshipment model
definition: An electricity transshipment model is a model that applies the transshipment problem to the electricity grid.

label: combined heat and power plant
definition: A combined heat and power plant (CHPP) is an energy transformation unit that consists of combined heat and power generating units, a grid component feeding electric energy into an electricity grid, and a grid component feeding thermal energy into a heating grid.

label: electrical conduction unit
definition: "A unit which represents a standard measurement of the movement of electrically charged particles through a transmission medium (electrical conductor)." [UOC:GVG]

label: renewable electrical energy
definition: Renewable electrical energy is electrical energy with a renewable origin.

label: bit
definition: "An information unit which refers to a digit in the binary numeral system, which consists of base 2 digits (ie there are only 2 possible values: 0 or 1)." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): residential
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'residential' is a household sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
All emissions from fuel combustion in households.

label: EU emission sector: ETS aviation
definition: The EU emission sector ETS aviation is a transport sector defined by an EU emission sector division that covers greenhouse gas emissions regulated by the European Union Emissions Trading System and that are emitted by stationary installations.

label: power-to-gas system
definition: A power-to-gas system is a power-to-fuel system that implements a power-to-gas process. A water electrolyser is participating in the power-to-gas process.

label: megabyte
definition: "An information unit which is equal to 1000 kB." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: current collector
definition: A current collector is an energy converting component that transfers electrical energy between a stationary conductor and a grid supplied electric vehicle.

label: test data set
definition: A test data set is a data set used for testing.

label: market exchange
definition: A market exchange is an organisation that has the market exchange role.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): SF6 and PFCs from other product use
personal living space
definition: A personal living space is a space requirement that one person uses for living.

label: direct equivalent method
definition: A direct equivalent method is a primary energy consumption calculation method that quantifies renewable and nuclear energies using its secondary energy content assuming no conversion losses.

label: water electrolysis process
definition: A water electrolysis process is an energy transformation that uses an electric current to decompose water into hydrogen and oxygen gas. Electrical energy is converted into chemical energy (and waste heat).

label: hub height
definition: Hub height is a quality of a wind energy converting unit that measures the distance between surface and centre-line of the wind rotor.

label: study design
definition: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

label: switchyard
definition: A switchyard is an electricity grid component that connects different levels of voltage

label: gasoline vehicle
definition: A gasoline vehicle is an internal combustion vehicle that has only a gasoline engine as motor for propulsion.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): total emissions excluding LULUCF
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'total emissions excluding LULUCF' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories. It encompasses the following IPCC 2006 sectors: energy; industrial processes and product use; agriculture; waste; and other.

label: railway
definition: A railway is a transport network component that can only be used by trains.

label: author
definition: An author is an agent that creates or has created written work.

label: biogasoline
definition: Biogasoline is a portion of matter that has a liquid state of matter and has a gasoline fuel role. It consists of bioethanol, biomethanol and products of these two substances. It is made from vegetable or animal material and thus has a biogenic origin.

label: memo item
definition: A memo item is an information content entity about a sector that describes that the sector is excluded from some kind of total and only reported to provide further information (memo).

label: hectare
definition: "An area unit which is equal to an area of 10,000 square meters. Equivalent to 2.471 acres." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: nitrogen dioxide
definition: Nitrogen dioxide is a portion of matter with the chemical formula NO2. It is a gas and can act as an air pollutant.

label: construction time
definition: A construction time is a time span that measures the time that is needed to construct an artificial object.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): injection and storage
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'pipelines' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Fugitive emissions from activities and equipment at the injection site and those from the end containment once the CO2 is placed in storage.

label: data preprocessing
definition: Data preprocessing is data processing that transforms the input into a form that is useable for a model calculation.

label: market participant
definition: A market participant is an agent who participates in trading in a market exchange.

label: state of matter
definition: A state of matter is a quality of a portion of matter that describes the distinct physical form in which the matter exists.

label: NC/BR sector: waste management/waste
definition: The NC/BR sector "waste management/waste" is a waste and wastewater sector defined by an NC/BR sector division. It aligns to the CRF sector (IPCC 2006): waste.

label: document
definition: A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): multilateral operations
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'multilateral operation' is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions from fuels used for aviation and waterborne navigation in multilateral operations pursuant to the Charter of the United Nations.

label: offshore wind farm
definition: An offshore wind farm is a wind farm that is build in a body of water, usually the ocean.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): liming
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'liming' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
CO2 emissions from the use of lime in agricultural soils, managed forest soils or lakes.

label: power unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure power or the rate of doing work." [NIST:NIST]

label: primary energy carrier
definition: A primary energy carrier is an energy carrier that has the disposition primary energy carrier disposition.

label: PHP
definition: PHP is a programming language designed by Rasmus Lerdorf.

label: wind variability identification
definition:
Wind variability identification is an action specification that describes the process of identifying variations in wind characteristics across temporal scales.
Wind characteristics include speed, direction, frequency, turbulence, and seasonal or diurnal patterns.

label: dam
definition: A dam is an artificial object that stops or restricts the flow of water or underground streams.

label: sodium-ion battery
definition: A sodium-ion battery is a rechargeable metal-ion battery that uses sodium ions as charge carriers.

label: hydrogen transport
definition: Hydrogen transport is the combustion fuel transport of hydrogen.

label: areal solar energy density
definition: An areal solar energy density is an areal energy density that gives the arriving solar energy per area. A synonym for areal solar energy density is irradiation.

label: hourly
definition: one value per hour

label: data licence
definition: A data licence is a licence that determines ownership, database protection, and permissions for data.

label: energy transformation function
definition: An energy transformation function is the function of an artificial object that has been engineered to transform input energy into usable output energy of a different type.

label: gasoline
definition: Gasoline (American English) or petrol (British English) is a portion of matter in the form of a transparent petroleum-derived liquid that is used primarily as a fuel in spark-ignited internal combustion engines. It consists mostly of organic compounds obtained by the fractional distillation of petroleum, enhanced with a variety of additives.

label: GovReg sector division
definition: The GovReg sector division is a sector division defined in Annex XXV, Table 1a of Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) 2020/1208. It uses CRF sectors (IPCC 2006) and adds further sectors.

label: gigawatt-hour
definition: A gigawatt-hour is a watt-hour based unit which is equal to 10^9 watt-hours.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): urea application
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'urea application' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories

label: renewable electrolytic hydrogen
definition: Renewable electrolytic hydrogen is electrolytic hydrogen that is produced with renewable electrical energy.

label: methanation
definition: A methanation is a redox reaction that converts carbon dioxide and hydrogen to synthetic methane and water.

label: marine thermal energy
definition: Marine thermal energy is a kind of natural ambient thermal energy that is present in marine water bodies.

label: crude oil
definition: Crude oil is a portion of mater of fossil origin comprising a mixture of hydrocarbons and associated impurities, such as sulphur. It exists in the liquid phase under normal surface temperature and pressure and its physical characteristics (density, viscosity, etc.) are highly variable. This category includes field or lease condensate recovered from associated and non-associated gas where it is commingled with the commercial crude oil stream.

label: solid biofuel
definition: Solid biomass is a portion of matter consisting of organic, non-fossil material of biological origin which may be used as fuel for heat production or electricity generation.

label: gross electricity generation
definition: Gross electricity generation is a process attribute that refers to the total amount of electrical energy produced in an electricity generation process.

label: political party
definition: A political party is an organisation of a group of people with common views or goals that wants to have influence in politics.

label: electricity generation function
definition: An electricity generation function is an energy transformation function to transform other types of energy to electrical energy.

label: greenhouse gas emission rate
definition: A greenhouse gas emission rate is an emission rate that describes the output of a greenhouse gas emission process.

label: newton
definition: "A force unit which is equal to the force required to cause an acceleration of 1m/s2 of a mass of 1 Kg in the direction of the force." [NIST:NIST]

label: calculate technical potential
definition: Calculate technical potential is an action specification that describes how the total energy production capability of the available area is determined, factoring in turbine placement, capacity density, and wake losses.

label: fuel role
definition: A fuel role is a role of a portion of matter that has the disposition to be an energy carrier and is used in a process that releases the carried energy by transforming the portion of matter into a different kind of portion of matter in a way that releases heat or does work.

label: petroleum coke
definition: Petroleum coke is a portion of matter with a solid state of matter that is produced in a mineral oil refining process. It consists mainly of carbon and can be uses as a fuel.

label: forecast
definition: A forecast is an information content entity that contains statements about the most probable future development predicted with the help of past and present data.

label: EU climate policy
definition: The EU climate policy is the policy of the European Union for reducing greenhouse gas emissions. It uses an EU emission sector division.

label: primary modelling purpose
definition: A primary modelling purpose is a model descriptor stating the main purpose of a model.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): domestic navigation
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'domestic navigation' is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions from fuels used by vessels of all flags that depart and arrive in the same country (exclude fishing, which should be reported under 1 A 4 c iii, and military, which should be reported under 1 A 5 b). Note that this may include journeys of considerable length between two ports in a country (e.g. San Francisco to Honolulu).

label: energy
definition: Energy is a quality of material entities which manifests as a capacity to perform work (such as causing motion or the interaction of molecules)

label: conventional energy
definition: A conventional energy is an energy that has a conventional origin.

label: social cost of emission
definition: Social cost of emission is the cost the society bears for an emission value.

label: discount rate
definition: A discount rate is an economic value with the unit percent that refers to the interest rate used in discounted cash flow (DCF) analysis to determine the present value of future cash flows.

label: transport network
definition: A transport network is a supply system of transport network components that enables the transport of people and/or goods.

label: decommissioning cost
definition: Decommissioning costs are investment costs arising from the decommissioning of a technological device at the end of its lifetime.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): solvents
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'solvents' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
HFCs and, to a much lesser extent PFCs, are being used as substitutes for ozone depleting substances (most notably CFC-113). Typical HFCs used are HFC-365mfc and HFC-43-10mee. Use of these fluorinated replacements is much less widespread than the ozone depleting substances they replace. Re-capture and re-use is also much more widely practiced The primary areas of use are precision cleaning, electronics cleaning, metal cleaning and deposition applications. Emissions from aerosols containing solvents should be reported undercategory 2F4 "Aerosols" rather than under this category.

label: peat
definition: Peat is a or portion of matter that is a soft, porous or compressed, sedimentary deposit of plant origin with high water content (up to 90 % in the raw state) and can be used as combustion fuel. As the natural formation of peat takes at least centuries, peat is usually considered having a fossil origin.

label: critical infrastructure role
definition: A critical infrastructure role is a role of artificial objects, such as plants and systems, that are assessed to be crucial for the preservation of societal functions, health, safety and economical or social welfare.

label: non-energy use
definition: Non-energy use is the consumption of an energy carrier without making use the energy it carries.

label: concentration unit
definition: "A unit which represents a standard measurement of how much of a given substance there is mixed with another substance." [UOC:GVG]

label: marine tidal energy power plant
definition: A marine tidal energy power plant is a power plant that has marine tidal energy units as parts.

label: analytical approach
definition: A analytical approach is a model descriptor that contains information about the analysis strategy of a model.

label: model intercomparison study
definition: A model intercomparison study is a scenario study that performs a comparison of several models using a reference scenario.

label: road network
definition: A road network is a transport network that enables transport on roads.

label: funder
definition: A funder is a sponsor that supports by giving money.

label: solar thermal heat technology
definition: A solar thermal heat technology is a heat generation technology that describes how to combine solar heat units, solar thermal energy transformation processes, energy carriers and energy in a specific way.

label: evaporation
definition: Evaporation is a phase transition from a liquid medium to their gaseous state.

label: onshore wind farm
definition: An onshore wind farm is a wind farm that is build on land.

label: negative emission
definition: Negative emission is the process of absorbing a substance, usually a pollutant that was emitted before.

label: scenario projection
definition: A scenario projection is an intentional process in which output (endogenous) data of interest are quantified for future points in time using one or more model calculation based on a scenario.

label: renewable
definition: Renewable is an origin of energies that replenish on a human time scale.

label: plasmatic
definition: The state of being a plasma. A portion of matter is in plasmatic state if and only if it has has no definite shape and no definite volume and is electrically conductive.

label: battery electric truck
definition: A battery electric truck is a truck that has an electric traction motor and a traction battery and thus is also a battery electric vehicle.

label: pico
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -12." [GVG:UO]

label: cost
definition: Cost is a quantity value that describes the amount of money needed to buy, make, or do a thing.

label: vehicle
definition: A vehicle is an artificial object that is used for transporting people or goods.

label: volume
definition: A volume is a quantity value indicating the size of a three-dimensional spatial region.

label: heating oil
definition: Heating oil is gas diesel oil for industrial and commercial uses, marine diesel and diesel used in rail traffic, other gas oil, including heavy gas oils which distil between 380 °C and 540 °C and which are used as petrochemical feedstocks.

label: variable cost
definition: A variable cost is a cost that depends on an amount of goods or services.

label: boolean variable
definition: A boolean variable is a variable that represents a boolean value.

label: wind energy transformation
definition: Wind energy transformation is an energy transformation that converts wind energy to electrical energy.

label: diesel vehicle
definition: A diesel vehicle is an internal combustion vehicle that has only a diesel engine as motor for propulsion.

label: transport network component
definition: A transport network component is an artificial object that is part of a transport network.

label: marine tidal energy technology
definition: A marine tidal energy technology is a marine hydro power technology that describes how to combine marine tidal energy converting units in marine tidal energy transformations.

label: markup
definition: A markup is a quantity value that indicates a virtual amount added to an assumed or historical price to predict a price in a different context.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): road transportation
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'road transport' is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
All combustion and evaporative emissions arising from fuel use in road vehicles, including the use of agricultural vehicles on paved roads.

label: sensible heat storage object
definition: A sensible heat storage object is a thermal energy storage object that stores thermal energy through temperature changes in some medium.

label: public funder
definition: A public funder is a funder that gives public money.

label: chemical reaction
definition: A chemical reaction is a transformation that involves the interconversion of chemical species.

label: micro
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -6." [UO:GVG]

label: terabyte
definition: "An information unit which is equal to 1000 gigabytes." [UO:GVG]

label: hydroelectric energy transformation
definition: Hydroelectric energy transformation is a hydro energy transformation that converts hydro energy to electrical energy.

label: graphical user interface
definition: A graphical user interface (GUI) is a software interface allowing users to communicate with a software application through a graphical window.

label: biogenic
definition: Biogenic is an origin of portions of matter made by or produced from life forms.

label: diffuse solar radiation
definition: Diffuse solar radiation is radiation that is the part of solar radiation that has been scattered by gas molecules in the atmosphere and by particles such as cloud droplets and aerosols.

label: wind
definition: Wind is a process of air naturally moving.

label: power-to-gas process
definition: A power-to-gas process is a power-to-fuel process that converts electrical energy to chemical energy by synthesising portions of matter into a gaseous synthetic fuel.

label: economy
definition: An economy is a system of production, distribution, trade and consumption of goods and services.

label: total emissions including LULUCF and including international aviation
definition: 'Total emissions excluding LULUCF and including international aviation' is a sector that 'CRF sector (IPCC 2006): total emissions including LULUCF' and 'CRF sector (IPCC 2006): international aviation'.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): other applications
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'other applications' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
The properties of ozone depleting substances have made them attractive for a variety of niche applications not covered in other sub-source categories. These include electronics testing, heat transfer, dielectric fluid and medical applications. The properties of HFCs and PFCs are equally attractive in some of these sectors and they have been adopted as substitutes. There are also some historical uses of PFCs, as well as emerging use of HFCs, in these applications. These applications have leakage rates ranging from 100% emissive in year of application to around 1% per annum.

label: water flow
definition: Water flow is a process of liquid water moving.

label: reference scenario
definition: A reference scenario is a scenario that is used as a reference, e.g. in a scenario comparison. It has the reference role.

label: solar thermal collector
definition: A solar thermal collector is a heater that converts solar energy to solar thermal energy.

label: ethanol
definition: Ethanol is a portion of matter with the chemical formula C2H6O. It has a liquid normal state of matter and can be used as a combustion fuel.

label: nitrogen trifluoride
definition: Nitrogen trifluoride is a portion of matter with the chemical formula NF3. It has a gaseous normal state of matter. It can work as a potent greenhouse gas and has an anthropogenic origin.

label: rock
definition: A rock is a portion of matter that is a naturally occurring solid aggregate of minerals or mineraloid matter that is part of the earth's crust.

label: paper
definition: Paper is a portion of matter that is made from cellulose fibres and other plant materials. It is used for paper-based products. It has a solid normal state of matter. It is the physical output of an industrial process and has a commodity role.

label: specifically dependent continuant
definition: b is a specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region and which is such that b s-depends_on c at every time t during the course of b’s existence. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [050-003])

label: ratio
definition: "A dimensionless ratio unit which, given a pair of quantities a and b, for which b is a multiple of a, denotes b by giving the multiplier (coefficient) c for a to result in b." [UOB:LKSR]

label: start alignment
definition: A start alignment is a time stamp alignment indicating that the time stamp marks the start of the time step.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): transport
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'transport' is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions from the combustion and evaporation of fuel for all transport activity (excluding military transport), regardless of the sector, specified by sub-categories below. Emissions from fuel sold to any air or marine vessel engaged in international transport (1 A 3 a i and 1 A 3 d i) should as far as possible be excluded from the totals and subtotals in this category and should be reported separately.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): total emissions including LULUCF
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'total emissions including LULUCF' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories. It encompasses the following IPCC 2006 sectors: energy; industrial processes and product use; agriculture; land use, land-use change and forestry; waste; and other.

label: kinetic energy storage object
definition: A kinetic energy storage object is an energy storage object that has the function to store kinetic energy.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): other product manufacture and use
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'other product manufacture and use' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions of sulphur hexafluoride (SF6) and perfluorocarbons
(PFCs) from the manufacture and use of electrical equipment and a number of other products. It also includes emissions of nitrous oxide (N2O) from several products.

label: main activity energy producer
definition: A main activity energy producer is an organisational energy producer whose primary activity is electrical energy and/or heat production.

label: BSI-KritisV transport sector
definition: The BSI-KritisV transport sector is a transport sector defined by the BSI-KritisV sector division (§ 8 BSI-KritisV).

label: solar power plant
definition: A solar power plant is a power plant that has solar power units as parts.

label: physical unit
definition: A physical unit is a unit that represents a standardised quantity value of a physical quantifiable entity.

label: temperature
definition: Temperature is a quality representing the driving force for the flow of heat energy and is a measure of the heat content of a material entity.

label: steam-electric process
definition: A steam-electric process is an energy transformation that converts thermal energy to electrical energy. A steam turbine and an electro motive generator are participating in a steam-electric process.

label: diesel fuel
definition: A diesel fuel is a combustion fuel that has a diesel fuel role.

label: vehicle charging station
definition: A vehicle charging station is an electricity grid component that transfers electrical energy into the traction battery of a battery electric vehicle.

label: KSG sector buildings
definition:
The KSG sector buildings is a building sector defined by the KSG sector division. It is an aggregate of the following two sectors:
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): commercial and institutional (CRF 1.A.4.a)
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): residential (CRF 1.A.4.b)
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): fuel combustion - other

label: CO2 emission
definition: A CO2 emission is an emission that releases carbon dioxide.

label: symbol
definition: An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity.

label: hertz
definition: "A frequency unit which is equal to 1 complete cycle of a recurring phenomenon in 1 second." [NIST:NIST]

label: space requirement for construction
definition: A space requirement for construction is space requirement of an artificial object that covers the area needed in order to construct an artificial object.

label: ton of oil equivalent
definition: A ton of oil equivalent is an energy unit which is equal to the amount of energy released by burning one metric ton of crude oil with a certain net calorific value. That is defined as 41.868 gigajoules or 11.63 megawatt-hours.

label: data descriptor
definition: A data descriptor is an information content entity that contains additional information about some data.

label: energy transfer
definition: Energy transfer is an energy transformation in form of a spatial transmission, that does not change the types of energies, apart from losses, e.g. waste heat.

label: import price
definition: An import price is the monetary price for the import of a material entity.

label: climate neutral process
definition: A climate neutral process is a process that has a process climate neutrality attribute.

label: working age population
definition: The working age population is the population of people aged 15 to 65.

label: photovoltaic power plant
definition: A photovoltaic power plant is a solar power plant that has PV panels as parts.

label: exchange rate
definition: The exchange rate is an economic value representing the ratio at which one currency can be exchanged for another.

label: origin
definition: Origin is a quality of a portion of matter or energy based on where it comes from. It is inherited from its primary sources.

label: marine current energy power plant
definition: A marine current energy power plant is a power plant that has marine current energy units as parts.

label: three dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum
definition: A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses three values to specify a position within a three dimensional spatial region

label: distribution
definition: Distribution is the process of delivering goods and services to agents. ETst

label: compressed gas fuel
definition: A compressed gas fuel is a combustion fuel that has a compressed gas fuel role.

label: liquefied petroleum gas
definition: Liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) is gas mixture of hydrocarbon gases, mainly propane and butane.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): waste - other
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'waste - other' is a waste and wastewater sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories

label: climate scenario
definition: A climate scenario is a scenario that describes a possible future state of a climate system.

label: marine current energy
definition: Marine current energy is the natural hydro energy of an ocean current.

label: transformative measure
definition: A transformative measure is a process that is an activity that has a direct impact on a specific variable in question.

label: directive information entity
definition: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

label: motorcycle
definition: A motorcycle is a motorised road vehicle that has two wheels.

label: steam reforming
definition: A steam reforming process is a chemical reaction that converts hydrocarbons and steam to syngas. As it converts chemical energy and thermal energy to a different type of chemical energy (and waste heat), it is also an energy transformation process.

label: latent heat storage object
definition: A latent heat storage object (LHS) is a thermal energy storage object that stores thermal energy through phase transitions in phase-change materials (PCM).

label: ontological uncertainty
definition: Ontological uncertainty is a nature of model uncertainty that stems from inherent variability of a phenomenon.

label: European Union Emissions Trading System
definition: The European Union Emissions Trading System (EU ETS) is a policy instrument that implements an emissions trading system covering the European Union, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein.

label: yocto
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -24." [UO:GVG]

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): aerosols
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'aerosols' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Most aerosol packages now contain hydrocarbon (HC) as propellants but, in a small fraction of the total, HFCs and PFCs may be used as propellants or solvents. Emissions from aerosols usually occur shortly after production, on average six months after sale. During the use of aerosols, 100% of the chemical is emitted. The 5 main sources are metered dose inhalers (MDIs), personal care products (e.g. hair care, deodorant, shaving cream), household products (e.g. air-fresheners, oven and fabric cleaners), industrial products (e.g. special cleaning sprays such as those for operating electrical contact, lubricants, pipe-freezers) and other general products (e.g. silly string, tire inflators, claxons), although in some regions the use of such general products is restricted. The HFCs currently used as propellants are HFC 134a, HFC 227ea, and HFC 152a. The substance HFC 43 10mee and a PFC, perfluorohexane, are used as solvents in industrial aerosol products.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): carbide production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'carbide production' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
The production of carbide can result in emissions of CO2, CH4, CO and SO2. Silicon carbide is a significant artificial abrasive. It is produced from silica sand or quartz and petroleum coke. Calcium carbide is used in the production of acetylene, in the manufacture of cyanamide (a minor historical use), and as a reductant in electric arc steel furnaces. It is made from calcium carbonate (limestone) and carbon-containing reductant (petroleum coke).

label: pollution
definition: Pollution is an emission with a negative effect on the environment or organisms.

label: cold start
definition: A cold start is a process in which an energy transformation unit is started-up after a period of inactivity.

label: decrease
definition: A process of becoming smaller, less numerous, less important, or less likely.

label: regulatory instrument
definition: A regulatory instrument is a policy instrument that stipulates rules made by a government (=institution) to control the way something is done.

label: specific space requirement
definition: A specific space requirement is a quantity value that indicates a certain space requirement per nameplate capacity.

label: climate neutrality criterion
definition: A climate neutrality criterion is a plan specification that intends to describe a state in which human activities result in no net effect on the climate system.

label: solar radiation receiving surface
definition: A solar radiation receiving surface is a surface that is receiving solar energy via solar radiation.

label: zepto
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -21." [UO:GVG]

label: passenger train station
definition: A passenger train station is a train station for the exchange of passengers.

label: comma separated file format
definition: A comma separated file format is a delimiter separated file format that uses comma (,) as delimiter.

label: energy storage unit
definition: An energy storage unit is a grid component that stores energy.

label: assumption
definition: An assumption is an information content entity about a property of a system or process. It determines a part of a scenario content.

label: determine annual energy yield
definition: Determine annual energy yield is an action specification that describes how a turbine's power curve is combined with the wind speed distribution to calculate the expected annual energy production.

label: heat transfer
definition: Heat transfer is an energy transfer of thermal energy.

label: power-to-fuel system
definition: A power-to-fuel system is an energy transformation unit that implements a power-to-fuel process. A water electrolyser is participating in the power-to-fuel process.

label: aerothermal energy
definition: Aerothermal energy is a natural ambient thermal energy that is stored in the air of a natural environment.

label: maximum value
definition: A maximum value is a quantity value that represents the upper limit of an artificial object or process to contain or transform another entity.

label: energy storage technology
definition: An energy storage technology is an energy technology that describes how to combine energy storage objects and energy carriers in charging and decharging processes for the purpose of temporarily storing energy.

label: action specification for wind farm development area
definition: Action specification for wind farm development area is an action specification that deals with available area for wind farm development.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): adipic acid production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'adipic acid production is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Adipic acid is used in the manufacture of a large number of products including synthetic fibres, coatings, plastics, urethane foams, elastomers and synthetic lubricants. The production of Nylon 6.6 accounts for the bulk of adipic acid
use. The main greenhouse gas emitted from adipic acid production is nitrous oxide.

label: lumen
definition: "A luminous flux unit which is equal to the luminous flux emitted into 1 steradian by a point source of 1 candela." [NIST:NIST]

label: grid-bound heating
definition: Grid-bound heating is a heat transfer over a distance via a heating grid, using steam or (hot) water.

label: objective specification
definition: A directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

label: power-to-methane system
definition: A power-to-methane system is a power-to-gas system that implements the power-to-methane process.

label: gas grid
definition: A gas grid is a supply grid that distributes gaseous fuel, e.g. methane.

label: surface azimuth angle
definition: A surface azimuth angle is a quantity value with a plane angle unit that measures the deviation of the projection on a horizontal plane of the normal to the plane from the local meridian, with zero due south, east negative, and west positive.

label: good role
definition: The role of an independent continuant or energy over which ownership rights can be established, whose ownership can be passed from one party to another by engaging in transactions, and that is not money.

label: steam power unit
definition: A steam power unit is a power generating unit that only has a steam turbine as turbine.

label: air pollutant
definition: An air pollutant is a portion of matter that participates in some air pollution.

label: quantity value
definition: A quantity value is an information content entity defined by a numeral together with a unit of measurement to quantify an entity.

label: compressed gas engine
definition: A compressed gas engine is a gas engine that uses a compressed gas fuel.

label: start-up speed
definition: Start-up speed is ramping during a cold start.

label: steam turbine
definition: A steam turbine is a turbine that converts heat from pressurised steam into rotational energy.

label: gigajoule
definition: An energy unit which is equal to 10^9 joules.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): mineral industry
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'mineral industry' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Process-related carbon dioxide (CO2) emissions resulting from the use of carbonate raw materials in the production and use of a variety of mineral industry products.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): enteric fermentation
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'enteric fermentation' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Methane emissions from herbivores as a by-product of enteric fermentation (a digestive process by which carbohydrates are broken down by micro-organisms into simple molecules for absorption into the bloodstream). Ruminant animals (e.g., cattle, sheep) are major sources with moderate amounts produced from non-ruminant animals (e.g., pigs, horses).

label: power system
definition: A power system is an energy system covering the generation, transportation, distribution and consumption of electrical energy.

label: liquid air
definition: Liquid air is air that has a liquid state of matter.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): solid waste disposal
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'solid waste disposal' is a waste and wastewater sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Methane is produced from anaerobic microbial decomposition of organic matter in solid waste disposal sites.

label: mega
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of million." [UO:GVG]

label: final energy carrier disposition
definition: Final energy carrier disposition is an energy carrier disposition of material entities that are delivered to energy consumers for their use.

label: port
definition: A port is a transport hub for ships.

label: ambiguous uncertainty
definition: Ambiguous uncertainty is a nature of model uncertainty that stems from multiple frames of reference about a phenomenon existing similtaneously.

label: refinery gas
definition: Refinery gas is a gas mixture that is produced as a by-product of a mineral oil refining process. It mainly consists of hydrogen, methane, ethane and olefins and can be used as a fuel.

label: gross national electricity consumption value
definition: A gross national electricity consumption value is an energy consumption value measuring the consumption of electrical energy in a spatial region (e.g. a country), including gross electricity generation plus electricity imports, minus electricity exports. It is part of the gross inland energy consumption.

label: carbon capture and storage
definition: Carbon capture and storage (CCS) is a process that combines carbon capture and carbon sequestration.

label: nuclear energy carrier disposition
definition: A nuclear energy carrier is an energy carrier used in nuclear power stations to produce heat for steam turbines. Heat is created when the nuclear fuel undergoes nuclear fission.

label: biogas power unit
definition: A biogas power unit is a biofuel power unit using biogas as fuel.

label: heat pump
definition: A heat pump is a heater that transforms low temperature heat to high temperature heat using external energy.

label: application programming interface
definition: An application programming interface (API) is a software interface allowing two software applications to communicate with each other.

label: client
definition: A client is an agent that receives a product or service.

label: heat transfer unit
definition: A heat transfer unit is a heat generating unit that contains a heat exchanger and not a heater.

label: good
definition: A good is a continuant that has the good role.

label: prosumer
definition: A prosumer is an agent who is producer and consumer at the same time.

label: gas fired power unit
definition: A gas fired power unit is a power generating unit using gas as fuel.

label: oxygen
definition: Oxygen is a portion of matter with the chemical formula O2. It has a gaseous normal state of matter.

label: considered region role
definition: A considered region role is the role of a region of relevance that is used in an analysis.

label: power line
definition: A power line is a grid component link that is an uninterrupted transmission system between two nodes in an electricity grid.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): international bunkers
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'international bunkers' is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories. It encompasses international aviation and maritime navigation.

label: study descriptor
definition: A study descriptor is a data descriptor that allows the annotation of study information within a scenario bundle by means of keywords from ontological terminology.

label: blast furnace gas
definition: Blast furnace gas is manufactured coal based gas produced during the combustion of coke in blast furnaces in the iron and steel industry. It is recovered and used as a fuel partly within the plant and partly in other steel industry processes or in power stations equipped to burn it. The quantity of fuel should be reported on a gross calorific value basis.

label: solar thermal power unit
definition: A solar thermal power unit is a solar power unit that has solar thermal collectors as parts.

label: train station
definition: A train station is a transport hub for trains.

label: charcoal
definition: Charcoal is a portion of matter produced from wood via pyrolysis. It has a solid state of matter and can be used as fuel.

label: CRF sectors (IPCC 2006)
definition: CRF sectors (IPCC 2006) is a version of the common reporting format that was used for national greenhouse gas inventories since the year 2015. It implements the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories (with some deviations).

label: production
definition: Production is the transformation process of combining various inputs in order to create an output that is a good.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): field burning of agricultural residues
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'field burning of agricultural residues' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
CO2 emissions from urea application

label: compressed natural gas
definition: Compressed natural gas (CNG) is natural gas that has been compressed.

label: hydro storage power plant
definition: A hydro storage power plant is a hydro power plant that uses the available hydro energy of a stationary water storage.

label: measurement datum
definition: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

label: hydrogen fuel cell
definition: A hydrogen fuel cell is a fuel cell that uses hydrogen.

label: solar electrical energy
definition: Solar electrical energy is electrical energy that is energy output of a solar energy transformation.

label: passenger-kilometre
definition: Passenger-kilometre is a transport performance unit for the accumulated transport distance of people where one passenger-kilometre equals the transport distance of 1 km for one person.

label: transport hub
definition: A transport hub is a transport network component that allows the exchange of people and/or goods.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): product uses as substitutes for ozone depleting substances
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'product uses as substitutes for ozone depleting substances' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Hydrofluorocarbons (HFCs) and, to a very limited extent, perfluorocarbons (PFCs), are serving as alternatives to ozone depleting substances (ODS) being phased out under the Montreal Protocol.

label: liquefied natural gas truck
definition: A liquefied natural gas truck is a truck that uses liquefied natural gas in a gas engine for propulsion and thus is also a liquefied natural gas vehicle.

label: marine wave energy transformation
definition: Marine wave energy transformation is a hydroelectric energy transformation that converts marine wave energy to electrical energy.

label: numerical computer model
definition: A numerical computer model is a mathematical model that is calculated by a computer.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): energy
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) energy is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
All GHG emissions arising from combustion and fugitive releases of fuels. Emissions from the non-energy uses of fuels are generally not included here, but reported under Industrial Processes and Product Use.

label: study factsheet
definition: A study factsheet is a factsheet that contains information about a scenario study.

label: electrical energy storage function
definition: An electrical energy storage function is an energy storage function with electrical energy as input and output.

label: superconducting magnetic energy storage
definition: A superconducting magnetic energy storage (SMES) is an energy storage object that stores electrical energy in the magnetic field of a superconducting magnet.

label: sufficiency
definition: Sufficiency is a plan specification for reducing, in absolute terms, the consumption and production of end-use products and services through changes in social practices in order to comply with environmental sustainability while ensuring an adequate social foundation for all people.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): lime production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'lime production' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Process-related emissions from the production of various types of lime (ISIC: D2694).

label: kelvin
definition: "A thermodynamic temperature unit which is equal to the fraction 1/273.16 of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water." [BIPM:BIPM, NIST:NIST]

label: liquefied natural gas vehicle
definition: A liquefied natural gas vehicle is a gas vehicle that uses liquefied natural gas as fuel.

label: independent continuant
definition: A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.

label: sensitivity analysis
definition: A sensitivity analysis is the process of comparing different model calculations based on a variation of input parameters (exogenous data items).

label: watercraft
definition: A watercraft is a vehicle that is driving through water.

label: fuel power technology
definition: A fuel-powered generation technology is a power technology that describes how to combine fuel-powered units in a fuel-powered electricity generation process.

label: optimisation model
definition: An optimisation model is a model that optimises a target function.

label: motor gasoline
definition:
Motor gasoline is gasoline consisting of a mixture of light hydrocarbons distilling between 35 °C and 215 °C. It is used as a fuel for land based spark ignition engines. Motor gasoline may include additives, oxygenates and octane enhancers, including lead compounds such as TEL and TML.

Includes motor gasoline blending components (excluding additives/oxygenates), e.g. alkylates, isomerate, reformate, cracked gasoline destined for use as finished motor gasoline.

label: kinetic energy storage technology
definition: An kinetic energy storage technology is an energy storage technology that describes how to combine kinetic energy storage objects and kinetic energy in charging and decharging processes.

label: geographic coordinate
definition: A geographic coordinate is an information content entity explicitly stating the geographic position of a zero-dimensional spatial region on Earth, by using a set of numbers with respect to a geographic coordinate system.

label: marine tidal energy
definition: Marine tidal energy is the natural hydro energy of a tidal flow.

label: product
definition: A product is a continuant that is either a good or a service product.

label: filling station
definition: A filling station is energy transformation unit that transfers fuel into the fuel tank of a vehicle.

label: coal power technology
definition: A coal power technology is a fuel-powered technology that describes how to combine coal power units and coal in a fuel-powered electricity generation process.

label: document part
definition: An information content entity that is part of a document.

label: agriculture, forestry and land use sector
definition: A agriculture, forestry and land use (AFOLU) sector is a sector that covers activities and natural processes from agriculture, forestry, land use and land use change.

label: greenhouse gas emission value
definition: A greenhouse gas emission value is an emission value that quantifies a greenhouse gas emission rate and has a mass unit.

label: KSG sector industry
definition:
The KSG sector industry is an industry sector defined by the KSG sector division. It is an aggregate of the following three sectors:
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): manufacturing industries and construction (CRF 1.A.2)
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): CO2 transport and storage (CRF 1.C)
- CRF sector (IPCC 2006): industrial processes and product use (CRF 2)

label: areal energy density
definition: An areal energy density is a quantity value that states a certain energy amount per area.

label: merit order
definition: A merit order is a plan specification that describes the dispatch ranking of power plants (electrical generation) based on ascending order of price.

label: cubic meter
definition: "A volume unit which is equal to the volume of a cube with edges one meter in length. One cubic meter equals to 1000 liters." [NIST:NIST]

label: maximum
definition: maximum value within a set of data values, e.g. in a time step or spatial region

label: compressed air
definition: Compressed air is air that has been compressed to store energy. To discharge energy, the air is expanded.

label: synthetic fuel
definition: A synthetic fuel is a fuel produced from one or more portion(s) of matter using electric energy.

label: Ruby
definition: Ruby is a programming language designed by Yukihiro Matsumoto.

label: diesel fuel role
definition: A diesel fuel role is a fuel role that expresses that a portion of matter can be used in a diesel engine.

label: heating and cooling sector
definition: A heating and cooling sector is a sector that covers heating and cooling activities.

label: economic scenario
definition: An economic scenario is a scenario that describes a possible future state of economic systems.

label: heating grid
definition: A heating grid is a supply grid that distributes thermal energy via circulating steam or liquids.

label: data file format
definition: A file format is a data format that describes how data is structured in a file.

label: objective function
definition: An objective function is an information content entity stating the function that should be maximised or minimised to solve a problem.

label: phase transition
definition: A phase transition is a transformation of a medium from a solid, liquid, or gas state to a different state.

label: R
definition: R is a programming language designed by Ross Ihaka and Robert Gentleman and the R Core Team.

label: with existing measures scenario
definition: A with existing measures scenario (WEM) is a policy scenario that includes policy instruments and transformative measures that have been adopted and implemented.

label: determine capacity factor
definition: Determine capacity factor is an action specification that describes the calculation of the capacity factor (CF), which represents the ratio of actual energy output to the maximum possible output over a given time period.

label: time step
definition: A time step is a one-dimensional temporal region that has a start time and an ending time and thus a finite duration.

label: areal solar power density
definition: An areal solar power density is an areal power density that indicates the arriving solar power per area. A synonym for areal solar power density is irradiance.

label: energy conversion performance
definition: Energy conversion performance is a process attribute describing the ratio between the non-heat input of an energy transformation and the outputs that are used.

label: nuclear power plant
definition: A nuclear power plant is a power plant that has nuclear power units as parts.

label: liquid-metal battery
definition: A liquid-metal battery is a battery that consists of two molten metal alloys separated by an electrolyte. The rechargeable batteries are used for electric vehicles and potentially also for grid energy storage.

label: chemical energy transfer
definition: Chemical energy transfer is an energy transfer of chemical energy.

label: emission certificate
definition: An emission certificate is a licence that permits its holder/owner a specific emission value. An emission certificate can be traded at a CO2 market exchange.

label: kilogram per cubic meter
definition: "A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in cubic meters." [UOC:GVG]

label: steam reforming hydrogen
definition: Steam reforming hydrogen is hydrogen that is a physical output of a steam reforming process.

label: megawatt-hour
definition: A megawatt-hour is a watt-hour based unit which is equal to 10^6 watt-hours.

label: photovoltaic energy transformation
definition: Photovoltaic energy transformation is a solar energy transformation that converts solar energy into electrical energy.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): harvested wood products
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'harvested wood products' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories
CO2 net emissions or removals resulting from Harvest Wood Products.

label: export price
definition: An export price is the monetary price for the export of a material entity.

label: planned availability
definition: Planned availability is a quality that describes the amount of time a power plant is planned to be operational per year.

label: solar heat unit
definition: A solar heat unit is a heat generating unit that has a solar collector.

label: passenger port
definition: A passenger port is a port for the exchange of passengers.

label: energy demand
definition: Energy demand is a demand for energy.

label: nuclear fission
definition: Nuclear fission is a process of nuclear reaction or a radioactive decay in which the nucleus of an atom splits into two or more smaller, lighter nuclei.

label: modus
definition: A modus is an information content entity describing the state of activity something has, e.g. active, inactive or passive.

label: kilometer per hour
definition: "A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 kilometer distance in one hour." [NIST:NIST]

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): solid fuels
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'solid fuels' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Includes all intentional and unintentional emissions from the extraction, processing, storage and transport of fuel to the point of final use.

label: user
definition: A user is an agent that employs an aid, tool or information system to achieve a goal/benefit.

Greenhouse gas emissions that result from the production of various inorganic and organic chemicals.

Emissions from combustion of fuels in industry. Also includes combustion for the generation of electricity and heat for own use in these industries.

label: steel

Lead production covers production by the sintering/smelting process as well as direct smelting. Carbon dioxide emissions result as a product of the use of a variety of carbon-based reducing agents in both production

Solid waste composting and other biological treatment. Emissions from biogas facilities (anaerobic digestion) with energy production are reported in the Energy Sector (1A4).

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): refrigeration and air conditioning
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'refrigeration and air conditioning' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Refrigeration and air-conditioning systems are usually classified in six application domains or categories. These categories utilise different technologies such as heat exchangers, expansion devices, pipings and compressors. The six application domains are domestic refrigeration, commercial refrigeration, industrial processes, transport refrigeration, stationary air conditioning, mobile airconditioning systems. For all these applications, various HFCs are selectively replacing CFCs and HCFCs. For example, in developed countries, HFC-134a has replaced CFC-12 in domestic refrigeration and mobile air conditioning systems, and blends of HFCs such as R-407C (HFC-32/HFC-125/HFC-134a) and R-410A (HFC-32/HFC-125) are replacing HCFC-22 mainly in stationary air conditioning. Other, non HFC substances are used to replace CFCs and HCFCs such as iso-butane in domestic refrigeration or ammonia in industrial refrigeration. HFC- 152a is also being considered for mobile air conditioning in several regions.

label: gasworks gas
definition:
Gasworks gas is manufactured coal based gas that covers all types of gases produced in public utility or private plants, whose main purpose is manufacture, transport and distribution of gas. It includes gas produced by carbonisation (including gas produced by coke ovens and transferred to gasworks gas), by total gasification with or without enrichment with oil products (LPG, residual fuel oil, etc.), and by reforming and simple mixing of gases and/or air, reported under the rows ‘from other sources’. Under the transformation sector identify amounts of gasworks gas transferred to blended natural gas which will be distributed and consumed through the natural gas grid.

The production of other coal gases (i.e. coke oven gas, blast furnace gas and oxygen steel furnace gas) should be reported in the columns concerning such gases, and not as production of gasworks gas. The coal gases transferred to gasworks plants should then be reported (in their own column) in the transformation sector in the gasworks plants row. The total amount of gasworks gas resulting from transfers of other coal gases should appear in the production line for gasworks gas.

[...]

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): grassland
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'grassland' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions and removals from rangelands and pasture land that is not considered cropland. It also includes systems with woody vegetation that fall below the threshold values used in the forest land category and are not expected to exceed them, without human intervention. The category also includes all grassland from wild lands to recreational areas as well as agricultural and silvi-pastural systems, subdivided into managed and unmanaged, consistent with national definitions.

Nitric acid is used as a raw material mainly in the manufacture of nitrogenous-based fertiliser.
