In addition to these gases, C2F6, C3F8 and c-C4F8 may also be used and emitted during the manufacture of thin and smart displays.

label: supply system
definition: A supply system is a system that connects producers and consumers.

label: terajoule
definition: An energy unit which is equal to 10^12 joules.

label: market revenue
definition: Market revenue is a quantity value that represents the income from a trade at a market exchange.

label: photovoltaic technology
definition: A photovoltaic technology is a power generation technology that describes how to combine photovoltaic panels in an electricity generation process with solar energy as input.

label: decarbonisation pathway
definition: A decarbonisation pathway is a policy that aims at long-term emissions reductions.

label: model
definition: A model is a continuant to represent a system and its behaviours in a simplified or idealised way.

label: project
definition: A project is a process to achieve a specified goal that is unique in the sum of its conditions like its goal, time and cost budget and its organisation.

label: nitrous oxide
definition: Nitrous oxide is a portion of matter with the chemical formula N2O. It has a gaseous normal state of matter. It occurs naturally in the atmosphere as a trace gas and it can work as a greenhouse gas.

label: coal power plant
definition: A coal power plant is a power plant that has coal power units as parts.

label: deep uncertainty
definition: Deep uncertainty is a level of model uncertainty at which one can enumerate multiple alternatives, without being able to rank them in order of likelihood.

label: daily
definition: one value per day

label: checking against empirical data
definition: Checking against empirical data is a validation where something gets checked against empirical data.

label: emission factor value
definition: An emission factor value is a fraction value that quantifies an emission factor as quotient of the emissions or removals of a gas per unit activity.

label: electric traction motor
definition: An electric traction motor is an electric motor used for propulsion.

label: parts per notation unit
definition: "A dimensionless concentration notation which describes the amount of one substance in another. It is the ratio of the amount of the substance of interest to the amount of that substance plus the amount of the substance." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: transformer
definition: A transformer is an electricity grid component that passively transfers electrical energy from one electrical circuit to another.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): manufacture of solid fuels and other energy industries
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'manufacture of solid fuels and other energy industries' is an energy transformation sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Combustion emissions from fuel use during the manufacture of secondary and tertiary products from solid fuels including production of charcoal.

label: licence provider
definition: A licence provider is an agent that provides a licence that allows a licensee to do something specific.

label: joule
definition: "An energy unit which is equal to the energy required when a force of 1 newton moves an object 1 meter in the direction of the force." [NIST:NIST]

label: fueled power plant
definition: A fueled power plant is a power plant that has fueled power units as parts.

label: population
definition: A population is an aggregate of people in a spatial region.

label: parts per million
definition: "A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000 regardless of the units of measure used as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[6]." [UOC:GVG]

label: study subregion role
definition: A study subregion role is a study region role that refers to a subregion.

label: social cost of carbon emission
definition: Social cost of carbon emission is the cost the society bears for a greenhouse gas emission value.

label: gas diesel oil
definition: Gas/diesel oil is a portion of matter that is primarily a medium distillate distilling between 180 °C and 380 °C. Includes blending components. Several grades are available depending on uses.

label: energy market exchange
definition: An energy market exchange is a market exchange in which energy commodities are traded.

label: tera
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of ten to the power of 12." [UO:GVG]

label: electricity import
definition: Electricity import is the import of electrical energy.

label: PV panel
definition: A PV panel (photovoltaic panel) is a solar power unit absorbing sunlight as a source of energy to generate electricity.

label: delivery time
definition: Delivery time is a one-dimensional temporal region expressing the amount of time that it takes for goods that have been bought to arrive at the place where they are wanted.

label: public transport
definition: A public transport is a passenger transport in which a number of passengers share a common vehicle.

label: top down
definition: Top down is an analytical approach where design starts from the system as a whole. The system is then divided into smaller sub-applications with more details. Each part again goes through the top down approach till the complete system is designed with all minute details. Top down approach is also termed as breaking the bigger problem into smaller problems and solving them individually in a recursive manner. A top down model is based on a decomposition approach.

label: power plant with electro motive generator
definition: A power plant with electromotive generator is a power plant that has an electro motive generator.

label: kilowatt-hour
definition: "An energy unit which is equal to 1,000 watt-hours." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: study report due to legal obligation
definition: A study report due to legal obligation is a study report that is created beacause of a legal obligation.

label: rotational frequency unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the number of rotations in a given time." [NIST:NIST]

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): CO2 transport and storage
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'CO2 transport and storage' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Carbon dioxide (CO2) capture and storage (CCS) involves the capture of CO2 from anthropogenic sources, its transport to a storage location and its long-term isolation from the atmosphere. Emissions associated with CO2 transport, injection and storage are covered under category 1C. Emissions (and reductions) associated with CO2 capture should be reported under the IPCC Sector in which capture takes place (e.g. Fuel Combustion or Industrial Activities).

label: fee
definition: A fee is a quantity value that represents an amount of money paid for a  particular piece of work or for a particular right or service.

label: economic flow potential
definition: An economic flow potential is a type of flow potential that identifies the proportion of the technological potential that can be utilised economically (based on economic boundary conditions).

label: electric current unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the flow of electric charge." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: power generation technology
definition: A power generation technology is an energy technology that describes how to combine power generating units and energy carriers in a power generation process to generate electrical energy.

label: emission rate
definition: An emission rate is a process attribute that describes the output of an emission process.

label: instantaneous
definition: value measured at or modelled for exactly one 0-dim temporal region, referenced by a time stamp, e.g. to represent a time step in a time series

label: scenario factsheet
definition: A scenario factsheet is a factsheet that contains information about a scenario.

label: motorised road vehicle
definition: A motorised road vehicle is a road vehicle that has a traction motor.

label: hybrid
definition: Hybrid is an analytical approach that combines the top down and the bottom up approach. Some parts are based on composition approach while other parts are based on decomposition approach.

label: tunnel
definition: A tunnel is a transport network component that is built through a certain environment (e.g. a mountain or water) and allows to pass through that environment.

label: CO2 emission certificate price
definition: A CO2 emission certificate price is an emission price of an CO2 emission certificate that allows the emission of certain CO2 emission value.

label: waste role
definition: A waste role is a role of a material entity that has been discarded after primary use.

label: pi
definition: "A dimensionless unit which denoted an irrational real number, approximately equal to 3.14159 which is the ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter in Euclidean geometry." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: fraction value
definition: A fraction value is a relational quantity value that has a fraction as it's unit.

label: levy
definition: A levy is an economic instrument that consists of a compulsory financial charge imposed on an agent or institution by a governmental organisation.

label: femto
definition: "A prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of 10 to the power of -15." [UO:GVG]

label: trader
definition: A trader is a market participant that engages in the transfer of financial assets in any financial market on behalf of a client or a financial services provider.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): rice cultivation
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'rice cultivation' is an agriculture, forestry and land use sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Methane (CH4) emissions from anaerobic decomposition of organic material in flooded rice fields.

label: solar thermal energy transformation
definition: Solar thermal energy transformation is a solar energy transformation that converts solar energy into thermal energy.

label: compressed gas fuel role
definition: A compressed gas fuel role is a fuel role that expresses that a portion of matter can be used in a compressed gas engine.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): ferroalloys production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'ferroalloys' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Ferroalloys production covers emissions from primary metallurgical reduction production of the most common ferroalloys, i.e. ferro-silicon, silicon metal, ferro-manganese, silicon manganese, and ferro-chromium, excluding those
emissions relating to fuel use. From the production of these alloys, carbon dioxide (CO2), nitrous oxide (N2O), and methane (CH4) originating from ore- and reductant raw materials, is emitted.

label: material entity
definition: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

label: perfluorocarbon
definition: Perfluorocarbons (PFCs) are portions of matter consisting of organic compounds that contain fluorine atoms but no hydrogen atoms.

label: compressed gas truck
definition: A compressed gas truck is a truck that uses compressed gas in a gas engine for propulsion and thus is also a compressed gas vehicle.

label: liquid combustion fuel
definition: A liquid combustion fuel is a combustion fuel that has a liquid state of matter under normal conditions.

label: secondary energy production
definition: Secondary energy production is the production of secondary energy carriers.

label: base unit
definition: "A unit which is one of a particular measure to which all measures of that type can be related." [NIST:NIST]

label: feed-in tariff
definition: A feed-in tariff is an economic instrument designed to stimulate investment in renewable energy technologies by offering long-term contracts to agents who are producers of renewable energy.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): zinc production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'zinc production' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Zinc production covers emissions from both primary production of zinc from ore as well as recovery of zinc from scrap metals, excluding emissions related to fuel use. Following calcination, zinc metal is produced through one of three methods; 1-electro-thermic distillation, 2-pyrometallurgical smelting or 3-electrolysis. If method 1 or 2 is used, carbon dioxide (CO2) is emitted. Method 3 does not result in carbon dioxide emissions. Recovery of zinc from metal scrap often uses the same methods as primary production and may thus produce carbon dioxide emissions, which is included in this section.

label: radiative energy
definition: Radiative energy is energy that has been transmitted by a radiation process.

label: subsurface collector
definition: A subsurface collector is a heat exchanger that transfers ambient thermal energy to a working fluid. It consists of plastic pipes laid horizontally under the ground.

label: textual entity
definition: A textual entity is a part of a manifestation (FRBR sense), a generically dependent continuant whose concretizations are patterns of glyphs intended to be interpreted as words, formulas, etc.

label: solar energy
definition: Solar energy is radiative energy of the sun.

label: sector division
definition: A sector division is a specific way to subdivide a system.

label: geothermal power unit
definition: A geothermal power unit is a power unit using geothermal heat.

label: EU emission sector division
definition: An EU emission sector division is an EU legislation sector division used in the EU climate policy.

label: CO2 emission value
definition: A CO2 emission value is a greenhouse gas emission value that quantifies a CO2 emission rate and has a mass unit.

label: technological flow potential
definition: A technological flow potential is a type of a flow potential derived from a theoretical flow potential, taking account of the annual efficiency of the respective conversion technology and the additional restrictions regarding the area that is realistically available for energy generation.

label: compressor station
definition: A compressor station is an energy transformation unit that has a compressor to enable gas transport via a gas grid.

label: fossil
definition: Fossil is a geogenic origin of portions of matter created from organic material by geological processes lasting thousands or millions of years.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): domestic aviation
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'domestic aviation' is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Emissions from civil domestic passenger and freight traffic that departs and arrives in the same country (commercial, private, agriculture, etc.), including take-offs and landings for these flight stages. Note that this may include journeys of considerable length between two airports in a country (e.g. San Francisco to Honolulu). Exclude military, which should be reported under 1 A 5 b.

label: subsector
definition: A subsector is a sector that is a part of an other sector.

label: conventional trader
definition: A trader that trades the power of fossil fuel power plants.

label: hydro power plant
definition: A hydro power plant is a power plant having an aggregate of hydro power generating units as its power generating unit parts.

label: process climate neutrality
definition: Process climate neutrality is a process attribute that conforms to some climate neutrality criteria.

label: region of relevance
definition: A region of relevance is a spatial region that is used in a study or analysis, or is part of spatial planning.

label: fossil hydrogen
definition: Fossil hydrogen is hydrogen with fossil origin.

label: fuel cell electric truck
definition: A fuel cell electric truck is a truck that has an electric traction motor and uses electrical energy from a fuel cell and thus is also a fuel cell electric vehicle.

label: bottom up
definition: Bottom up is an analytical approach where parts of the system are defined in details. Once these parts are designed and developed, then these parts or components are linked together to prepare a bigger component. This approach is repeated until the complete system is built. A bottom up model is based on a composition approach.

label: typical year
definition: A typical year is a typical period with the duration of one year.

label: fossil combustion fuel
definition: A fossil combustion fuel is a combustion fuel with the origin fossil.

label: marine tidal energy converting unit
definition: A marine tidal energy converting unit is a hydro power unit that uses marine tidal energy.

label: pumped hydro storage power plant
definition: A pumped hydro storage power plant is a hydro storage power plant which has some pumps as parts.

label: time span
definition: A time span is a quantity value indicating the duration of a one-dimensional temporal region, measured in a time unit.

label: citation reference
definition: A citation reference is a reference stating where a citation was taken from.

label: nuclear power technology
definition: A nuclear power generation technology is a power generation technology that describes how to combine nuclear power units and nuclear fuel in an electricity generation process.

label: typical day
definition: A typical day is a typical period with the duration of one day.

label: PtL fuel
definition: PtL fuel is a liquid synthetic fuel produced in a power-to-liquid system from water and carbon dioxide using electrical energy.

label: sodium-sulphur battery
definition: A sodium–sulphur battery is a type of molten-salt battery constructed from liquid sodium (Na) and sulphur (S). This type of battery has a high energy density, high efficiency of charge/discharge and long cycle life, and is fabricated from inexpensive materials. The operating temperatures of 300 to 350 °C and the highly corrosive nature of the sodium polysulphides, primarily make them suitable for stationary energy storage applications. The cell becomes more economical with increasing size.

label: bicycle
definition: A bicycle is a road vehicle that has two wheels and is propelled by a person.

label: NC/BR sector division
definition:
The NC/BR sector division is a CRF-based sector division defined by the UNFCCC reporting guidelines on national communications for Parties included in Annex I to the Convention.
(https://unfccc.int/sites/default/files/resource/cp2019_13a01_adv.pdf, 6/CP.25, VI, Table 2)

label: study
definition: A study is a project with the goal to methodologically investigate something.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): magnesium production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'magnesium production' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Magnesium production covers GHG emissions related to both primary magnesium production as well as oxidation protection of magnesium metal during processing (recycling and casting), excluding those emissions relating to fuel use. In the primary production of magnesium, carbon dioxide (CO2) is emitted during calcination of dolomite and magnesite raw materials. Primary production of magnesium from non-carbonate raw materials does not emit carbon dioxide. In the processing of liquid magnesium, cover gases containing carbon dioxide (CO2), sulphur hexafluoride (SF6), the hydrofluorocarbon HFC 134a or the fluorinated ketone FK 5-1-12 ( C3F7C(O)C2F5) may be used. Partial
thermal decomposition and/or reaction between these compounds and liquid magnesium generates secondary compounds such as perfluorocarbons (PFCs), which are emitted in addition to unreacted cover gas constituents.

label: contract
definition: A contract is a document that contains an agreement between two or more competent agents to which those agents agree to be legally bound.

label: information unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of information." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: truck
definition: A truck is a motorised road vehicle that is used for freight transport.

label: tube collector
definition: A tube collector is a solar thermal collector that consists of tubes.

label: energy market model
definition: An energy market model is a model that is about the energy market.

label: uncertainty approach
definition: An uncertainty approach is a model descriptor that specifies how a model deals with uncertainty.

label: power-to-fuel technology
definition: A power-to-fuel technology is an energy technology that describes how to combine power-to-fuel systems in power-to-fuel processes.

label: energy unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the work done by a certain force (gravitational, electric, magnetic, force of inertia, etc)." [NIST:NIST]

label: data preparation
definition: Data preparation is an action specification that describes the steps the bearer takes to acquire raw data and how this data is cleaned, transformed, and structured for subsequent analysis. So it includes the acquisition and pre-processing of data.

label: molten-salt battery
definition: A molten-salt battery is a battery that uses molten salts as an electrolyte and offers both a high energy density and a high power density.

label: empirical data set
definition: An empirical data set is a dataset that is obtained from observations in the real world.

label: household sector
definition: A household sector is a sector that covers households.

label: synthetic
definition: Synthetic is an anthropogenic origin of portions of matter created artificially by a chemical process.

label: renewable power plant
definition: A renewable power plant is a power plant that has renewable power units as parts.

label: nuclear power unit
definition: A nuclear power unit is a power generating unit using nuclear fuel.

label: biogenic industrial waste fuel
definition: A biogenic industrial waste fuel is an industrial waste fuel that has a biogenic origin.

label: bidding zone role
definition: A bidding zone role is a role of a two-dimensional spatial region that is realised in market participants trading energy without capacity allocation.

label: hydrogen power unit
definition: A hydrogen power unit is a power generating unit using hydrogen as fuel.

label: density unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the influence exerted by some mass." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: methanol
definition: Methanol is a hydrocarbon with the chemical formula CH3OH. It has a liquid normal state of matter. As it can be oxidised it can be used as a fuel.

label: freight train station
definition: A freight train station is a train station for the exchange of goods.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): heat transfer fluid
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'heat transfer fluid' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Heat transfer fluids, which include several fully fluorinated carbon compounds (either in pure form or in mixtures) with six or more carbon atoms, used and emitted during IC manufacture, testing and assembly. They are used in chillers, temperature shock testers and vapour phase reflow soldering.

label: heat generation function
definition: A heat generation function is an energy transformation function to transform other types of energy to thermal energy.

label: energy transformation unit
definition: An energy transformation unit is an artificial object that transforms, changes or transfers a certain type of energy.

label: PM10
definition: PM10 is particulate matter which passes through a size-selective inlet as defined in the reference method for the sampling and measurement of PM10, EN 12341, with a 50 % efficiency cut-off at 10 µm aerodynamic diameter.

label: power
definition: Power is the process attribute that is the amount of energy transformed or transferred per time unit.

label: solar thermal power technology
definition: A solar thermal power technology is a power generation technology that describes how to combine solar thermal power units in an electricity generation process with solar energy as input.

label: energy storage capacity
definition: An energy storage capacity is the quantity value stating the maximum energy an energy storage object can store.

label: Eurostat energy balance sector division
definition:
The concept of "energy balance" is an accounting framework for the compilation and understanding of data on all energy products entering, exiting and being used in a country. The energy balance is the most complete statistical accounting of energy products and their flow in the economy. Columns of the energy balance represent energy products (fuels). Rows represent energy flows.

The energy balance expresses all forms of energy in a common accounting unit. The balance shows the relationships between supply, inputs to the energy transformation processes and their outputs as well as the actual energy consumption by different sectors of end-use.

label: nitrogen oxides
definition: Nitrogen oxides are a portion of matter consisting of compounds of nitrogen and oxygen. It is a collective term for numerous oxides of nitrogen with a gaseous normal state of matter. They can act as air pollutants.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): pipeline transport
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'pipeline transport' is a transport sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Combustion related emissions from the operation of pump stations and maintenance of pipelines. Transport via pipelines includes transport of gases  liquids, slurry and other commodities via pipelines. Distribution of natural or manufactured gas, water or steam from the distributor to final users is excluded and should be reported in 1 A 1 c ii or 1 A 4 a.

label: ton-kilometre
definition: Ton-kilometre is a transport performance unit for the accumulated transport distance of goods where one ton-kilometre equals the transport distance of 1 km for one ton of goods.

label: feasible potental determination process
definition: Feasible potential determination process al is a process that follows a determination methodology for feasable potential to gain knowledge of the feasible potential of something.

label: power plant operator
definition: A power plant operator is an agent that operates an electric utility generation station.

label: candela
definition: "A luminous intensity unit which equal to the luminous intensity, in a given direction, of a source that emits monochromatic radiation of frequency 540 x 1012 hertz and that has a radiant intensity in that direction of 1/683 watt per steradian." [BIPM:BIPM, NIST:NIST]

label: MMR sector division
definition: The MMR sector division is an EU emission sector division defined in Annex XII, Table 1 of Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) 749/2014. It uses CRF sectors (IPCC 2006) and adds further sectors.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): cement production
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'cement production' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
Process-related emissions from the production of various types of cement (ISIC: D2694).

label: renewable energy transformation function
definition: A renewable energy function is the energy transformation function to transform renewable energy.

label: annual
definition: one value per year

label: start time
definition: A start time is a zero-dimensional temporal region that indicates the beginning of a one-dimensional temporal region.

label: potential energy storage technology
definition: An potential energy storage technology is an energy storage technology that describes how to combine potential energy storage objects and potential energy in charging and decharging processes.

label: sub bituminous coal
definition: Sub bituminous coal is coal that is non-agglomerating with a gross calorific value between 17 435 kJ/kg (4 165 kcal/kg) and 23 865 kJ/kg (5 700 kcal/kg) containing more than 31 % volatile matter on a dry mineral matter free basis.

label: creative work licence
definition: A creative work licence is a copyright license that determines ownership and permissions for literary work and multimedia work that combines various media types such as text, audio, images, animations, video and interactive content and its collections.

label: market exchange role
definition: A role of an organisation, association, or group of persons, whether incorporated or unincorporated, which constitutes, maintains, or provides a facility for bringing together purchasers and sellers of financial instruments, commodities, or other products, services, or goods, and includes the market place and facilities maintained by the exchange

label: life cycle assessment
definition: A life cycle assessment is a methodology to calculate and analyse environmental impacts of the life cycle of a material entity or process.

label: fueled power unit
definition: A fueled power unit is a power generating unit that uses fuel.

label: biomass
definition: Biomass is a portion of matter from plants or animals and has thus has a biogenic origin.

label: variable production cost
definition: Variable costs are costs that depend on the amount of goods or services produced and which are paid by the producer.

label: voluntary agreement instrument
definition: A voluntary agreement instrument is a policy instrument that uses voluntary instruments between a government (institution) and one or more private institutions. The agreement's goal is to ensure transformative measures by the participating private institutions.

label: turns per second
definition: "A rotational frequency unit which is equal to the number complete turn in a period of time that equals to 1 second." [NIST:NIST]

label: power rating
definition: A power rating is a maximum value stating the maximum power an energy converting component can convert.

label: installation guide
definition: An installation guide is a documentation intended to help users install a Software.

label: luminous intensity unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the wavelength-weighted power emitted by a light source in a particular direction." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: tax
definition: A tax is a levy whose returns are used by the government to finance expenditures for the common welfare.

label: onshore wind power technology
definition: An onshore wind power technology is a wind power generation technology that describes how to use wind energy converting units in onshore wind farms.

label: compressed gas car
definition: A compressed gas car is a car that uses compressed gas in a gas engine for propulsion and thus is also a compressed gas vehicle.

label: compressed synthetic methane
definition: Compressed synthetic methane is synthetic methane that has been compressed.

label: electricity cost
definition: An electricity cost is a variable cost that depends on electricity price and amount.

label: geothermal heat plant
definition: A geothermal heat plant is a heat plant that has geothermal heat units as parts.

label: tertiary control
definition: A tertiary control is a frequency control that is either automated or manual. It takes over from secondary control to equalise electricity supply and demand imbalances that last for more than 15 minutes.

label: electric charge
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the quantity of unbalanced electricity in a body (either positive or negative) and construed as an excess or deficiency of electrons." [WordNet:WordNet]

label: uranium
definition: Uranium is a portion of matter that has the atomic number 92. It is a silver-grey metal.

label: spatial resolution
definition: Spatial resolution is the resolution of a georeferenced dataset that indicates the geographical level of detail.

label: grid supplied electric vehicle
definition: A grid supplied electric vehicle is an electric vehicle that has a current collector to use electrical energy.

label: direct solar radiation
definition: Direct solar radiation is radiation that is the non-scattered part of solar radiation from the sun within the extent of the solar disk only.

label: hour
definition: "A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

label: gas grid component
definition: A gas grid component is a grid component that is part of a gas grid.

label: areal energy density unit
definition: An areal energy density unit is a unit which is a measure for the energy per surface area.

label: areal power density unit
definition: An areal power density unit is a unit which is a measure for the power per surface area.

label: air pollution
definition: Air pollution occurs when harmful or excessive quantities of substances including gases, particles, and biological molecules are introduced into Earth's atmosphere.

label: hydrocarbon
definition: Hydrocarbon is a portion of matter which is member of class of organic chemical compounds composed only of the elements carbon (C) and hydrogen (H).

label: coking coal
definition: Coking coal is hard coal that is bituminous with a quality that allows the production of a coke suitable to support a blast furnace charge. Its gross calorific value is greater than 23 865 kJ/kg (5 700 kcal/kg) on an ash-free but moist basis.

label: time stamp
definition: A time stamp is a data descriptor that is used to describe either a temporal region or a data item that is related to a temporal region, e.g. a time stamped measurement datum. If the time stamp refers to a time step/one-dimensional temporal region, the indication of a time stamp alignment is required

label: heat generation technology
definition: A heat generation technology is an energy technology that describes how to combine heat generating units, heat generation processes, energy carriers and energy in a specific way.

label: solar radiation
definition: Solar radiation is radiation that is emitted by the sun.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): CO2 emissions from biomass
definition: The CRF sector (IPCC 2006): 'CO2 emissions from biomass' is a sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories: CO2 emissions from biomass combustion are not included in national totals, but are recorded as an information item for cross-checking purposes as well as avoiding double counting.

label: fluorinated greenhouse gas
definition: A fluorinated greenhouse gas is a greenhouse gas that is produced by fluorination. Hence it contains Fluor (F) atoms and is of anthropogenic origin.

label: temporal resolution
definition: Temporal resolution is the resolution of a time series that indicates time-dependent the level of detail.

label: aviation network
definition: An aviation network is a transport network that enables air transport.

label: area value
definition: An area value is a quantity value indicating the size of a two-dimensional spatial region.

label: generator
definition: A generator is an energy converting component that converts other forms of energy into electrical energy.

label: decommissioning start
definition: A decommissioning start is a start time that indicates the beginning of a decommissioning time.

label: block size
definition: Block size is the declared net capacity of a power generating unit.

label: Western Texas Intermediate
definition: Western Texas Intermediate (WTI) is a crude oil that is extracted on US territory and traded at NYMEX New York.

label: pressure unit
definition: "A unit which is a standard measure of the force applied to a given area." [NIST:NIST]

label: recycling
definition: Recycling is a material transformation that regains materials and/or energy from an artificial product or waste.

label: road
definition: A road is a transport network component with an artificial surface that allows transport for road vehicles.

label: fuel market exchange
definition: A fuel market exchange is an energy market exchange where fuels like oil, coal, renewable fuels, and natural gas are traded.

label: software module
definition: A software module is software composed of a collection of software methods.

label: gross inland energy consumption value
definition: A gross inland energy consumption value is an energy consumption value expressing the magnitude of the total consumption of energy in a spatial region (e.g. a country).

label: power-to-methane technology
definition: A power-to-methane technology is an power-to-gas technology that describes how to combine power-to-methane systems in power-to-methane processes.

label: energy transfer function

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): foam blowing agents
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'foam blowing agents' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
HFCs are being used as replacements for CFCs and HCFCs in foams, particularly in closed-cell insulation applications. Compounds that are being used include HFC-245fa, HFC-365mfc, HFC-227ea, HFC-134a, and HFC-152a. The processes and applications for which these various HFCs are being used include insulation boards and panels, pipe sections, sprayed systems and onecomponent gap filling foams. For open-cell foams, such as integral skin products for automotive steering wheels and facias, emissions of HFCs used as blowing agents are likely to occur during the manufacturing process. In closedcell foam, emissions not only occur during the manufacturing phase, but usually extend into the in-use phase and often the majority of emission occurs at the endof-life (de-commissioning losses). Accordingly, emissions can occur over a period of up to 50 years or even longer.

label: CRF sector (IPCC 2006): fire protection
definition:
The CRF sector (IPCC 2006) 'fire protection' is an industry sector defined by the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories:
There are two general types of fire protection (fire suppression) equipment that use greenhouse gases as partial replacements for halons: portable (streaming) equipment, and fixed (flooding) equipment. The non-ozone depleting, industrial gases HFCs, PFCs and more recently a fluoroketone are mainly used as substitutes for halons, typically halon 1301, in flooding equipment. PFCs played an early role in halon 1301 replacement but current use is limited to replenishment of previously installed systems. HFCs in portable equipment, typically replacing halon 1211, are available but have achieved very limited market acceptance due primarily to their high cost. PFC use in new portable extinguishers is currently limited to a small amount (few percent) in an HCFC blend.

It also includes systems with vegetation that currently fall below, but are expected to later exceed, the threshold values used by a country to define the forest land category.

emissions are not associated with primary aluminium production; however, casting of some high magnesium containing alloys does result in SF6 emissions and these emissions are accounted for in Section 2C4, Magnesium
